properties.name: NRMA Lake Somerset Holiday Park
properties.description:
Unplug and reconnect in the great outdoors
When it comes to adventure in the great outdoors, it’s hard to beat the classics. A tent or caravan set up in your chosen spot on the banks of a freshwater lake, where giant fish lurk. A boat ramp at your fingertips to get onto the water at first light. A place for the kids to roam free and plenty of activities to keep them busy. Communal cooking areas for fun-filled evenings under the stars with old friends and new.

At NRMA Lake Somerset Holiday Park, a great atmosphere is just the beginning. Our natural setting and back-to-basics approach is the perfect antidote to the daily grind, but we’ve thrown in enough comforts to make it easy – including lakeside cabins and glamping tents.

properties.name: NRMA Bowen Beachfront Holiday Park
properties.description:
A welcome escape by the sea
You’ve been daydreaming about this. Your caravan set up beside the sparkling waters of the Whitsunday Coast. Fishing, kayaking and ocean swimming on your doorstep. Remote islands fringed with vibrant coral reefs a stone’s throw away. A friendly atmosphere where sunny days fade into balmy tropical nights made for laughter and fun.

Welcome to NRMA Bowen Beachfront Holiday Park, where the good times flow as easily as the tides of the Coral Sea just metres from your cabin. We delight in entertaining you, with weekly activities for the whole family to enjoy. Think sunset sessions with gourmet snags and live music, for a start.

And when it comes to planning tomorrow’s island-hopping or beach-cruising adventure, our team is on-site to help you make the most of every moment.

properties.name: BIG4 Breeze Holiday Parks - Rainbow Beach
properties.description:
Rainbow Beach is a nature-lovers paradise. It’s the launch pad for the world’s largest sand island K’gari (Fraser Island). There’s epic fishing, coloured sands and a beach that doubles as a highway. The ultimate base for all this and more is BIG4 Breeze Holiday Parks – Rainbow Beach.

Just minutes from the holiday park is the centre of this seaside village with cafes, pubs and clubs boasting epic ocean views. Right next door is the town’s main boat ramp and with a choice of cabins, powered and unpowered sites, your next holiday should be a Breeze.

properties.name: Moreton Bay Cruise with Dolphin Feeding and Whale Watching
properties.description:
Head to Tangalooma Island Resort on this Moreton Bay Cruise from Brisbane to enjoy a whale watching cruise and dolphin feeding program at dusk. If you're fascinated by wildlife, you don't need to travel far to witness majestic wildlife in your own backyard.

Begin the day with a scenic cruise across Moreton Bay to the island where the whale watching adventure begins. Learn about Humpback Whales as they make their annual migration from June to October each year. Alighting from your three hour whale watching cruise after a tasty lunch, take advantage of the island's resort facilities, pools, restaurants and beaches while you wait for the sunset dolphin feeding program.

At dusk, local eco rangers will lead the dolphin feeding program as you venture in waist deep water to hand feed wild dolphins that pop by each night for their daily feed. Nothing can beat the extraordinary feeling of getting up close to dolphins and whales. Wrap up the day by taking a relaxing evening cruise back to Brisbane with a happy heart and extraordinary stories to tell.

properties.name: Brisbane Whale Watching Cruise
properties.description:
Join this 4.5 hour Brisbane whale watching cruise from Redcliffe and witness majestic Southern Humpback Whales on their annual migration to and from Antarctica between June and November in the Moreton Bay Marine Park. 

Step aboard the purpose built MV Eye Spy whale watching vessel with 6 spacious viewing decks, sun decks and floor to ceiling interior windows for unobstructed viewing of the Whales just metres from the boat. 
During the cruise, soak in the views of nearby Moreton Island while enjoying a delicious cold buffet lunch of Tiger Prawns, Ham, Roast Chicken, salads and bread rolls. The Brisbane Whale Watching Cruise departs from Redcliffe Jetty daily from 10am to 2.30pm. 

Don't miss out on Brisbane's whale watching season. Book online here for a close encounter with Southern Humpback Whales!

properties.name: Southern Cross Gold Coast Tours
properties.description:
Our tours are designed to enjoy the natural environment around us away from the crowds

Southern Cross Tours have been operating on the Gold Coast, Australia since 1994, and in this time have developed a range of Gold Coast tours where customers can experience a piece of the Gold Coast Hinterland and learn more about the environment and flora and fauna that call Australia home.

The point of difference is the uniqueness that these tours offer with exclusive venues, small, Modern, Luxury vehicles and travelling with a local guide who has grown up and lived in the areas visited on tour.

The tours are designed to enjoy the natural environment away from the crowds.

properties.name: Whale Watching Adventure Cruise from Noosa
properties.description:
Experience a close encounter with Humpback Whales during this 2 hour whale watching cruise from Noosa. Travelling aboard a rigid inflatable boat (RIB), 12 lucky passengers are in for an exciting ocean ride to witness these gentle giants of the ocean at sea level with uninterrupted views that only a small whale watching experience allows. 

See Humpback Whales as they make their annual migration from July to October when there is a greater chance to spot Humpback Whales and their calves bonding and playing in the waters surrounding Noosa as they travel back to Antarctica.

During this intimate cruise watch in awe as you witness common whale behaviours including a breach, tail slap and fluke up dive with entertaining commentary from guides. The Noosa Whale Watching Cruise is available daily from the Noosa Marina between July and October. Don't miss out an unforgettable wildlife experience this whale watching season - tickets available here.

**Highlights:**

-   2 hour whale watching cruise
-   Take in spectacular scenery and sights along the river
-   Small groups means that everyone gets a 'window seat'
-   See Hells Gates
-   A breathtaking indescribable experience
-   Experienced, informative and entertaining guide

properties.name: Noosa Surfing School and Lessons
properties.description:
There's only one way to get started, and that's to get in the water. However, a few helpful tips, the right equipment, and heaps of encouragement from your highly qualified instructor will go a long way with getting you hooked forever. 

You will learn in a relaxed, informal environment at your own pace while safe, gentle waves break in warm, waist-deep water. The water is vibrant blue and the sand is clean and white, making for a wonderful environment to admire and learn in.

Learn to Surf in Noosa caters to the complete beginner with no prior ocean experience necessary to fall in love with this popular Sunshine Coast past time. All you'll need to bring is a positive attitude and the ability to maybe laugh at yourself a couple of times when things don't immediately go perfectly! Your surfing lesson includes a 2 hour surf lesson, surf safety information, all necessary equipment including a soft beginner board, leg rope and a wetsuit or rashie and surf instruction to suit your skill level. If you're visiting the Sunshine Coast then learning to surf in Noosa is a definite must, you'll be having so much fun you won't want to return to shore! Book your lesson with Learn to Surf online today!

**Highlights:**

-   2 hour surf lesson
-   Be up and surfing in no time
-   Surf on famous Noosa Beach
-   All equipment supplied
-   Surf briefing and instruction
-   Surfing lessons in Noosa is a must do

properties.name: Noosa Dolphin View Kayak Tour
properties.description:
Embark on a scenic adventure along the coast to get up close to some of the region's most friendly and curious creatures on this multi-hour kayaking tour on the Sunshine Coast! Departing from Noosa, your adventure will begin with a picturesque 4-wheel-drive beach drive into the Great Sandy National Park and up to Double Island Point. This is the launching point for your enjoyable kayak in the warm, crystal clear waters. 

While on the water you'll have the chance to mingle with the likes of large Bottlenose Dolphin Pods, Humpback whales (between June and November), turtles, manta rays, sting rays and migrating sea birds to name a few.

Highlights:

-   Friendly and fun tour guides
-   4WD Great Beach Drive experience
-   90% strike rate with seeing dolphins
-   Breathtaking remote beaches
-   Light snacks and refreshments
-   Stunning views of beaches and sand cliffs

properties.name: Carnarvon Gorge Tours
properties.description:
Join this authentic Outback Queensland experience taking guests into the Carnarvon Gorge on a guided tour from Roma. Travel with ecologists to discover Aboriginal sites and natural rock formations, visit a working cattle property and embark on short walks in the outback. 

A delicious morning tea, lunch at Cycad Gorge and afternoon refreshments in a spectacular location are just some of the highlights you can expect on this guided Carnarvon Gorge day tour from Roma.

Highlights:

- Travel with an experienced ecologist
- Enjoy a picnic lunch of wholesome outback tucker
- Explore the hidden wonders & secluded gorges of the Carnarvon Ranges
- Take in breathtaking views of the Arcadia Valley
- A true and brilliant Outback Australian experience
- Visit unique cultural sites, including Aboriginal rock art

properties.name: Great Barrier Reef Snorkel Trip from Cape Tribulation
properties.description:
This half day eco tour visits two different snorkel destinations, each with an extraordinary array of marine life and coral species. 

After a fast 25 minute ride, guests are ready to snorkel two fabulous locations at Mackay and Undine Reefs. 

On most days, the rainforest can be seen along the mainland beach whilst snorkelling the Great Barrier Reef alongside sea turtles, which are found in abundance swimming over reefs full of colourful coral, along with myriads of tropical fish, eagle rays, giant clams and starfish.

**Highlights**  

-   Half day Great Barrier Reef Adventure
-   Visit 2 reef sites
-   2 hours snorkelling
-   Swim with turtles
-   Only 25 minutes to the reef
-   Small group experience

properties.name: Moreton Island Scuba Diving
properties.description:
Gear up and hit the waters of lovely Moreton Island off the coast of Brisbane for some quality snorkelling around the iconic Tangalooma Wrecks on this great value full day tour. 

You'll tour one of South East QLD's most popular and easily accessible dive spots - this is a great value way for divers both beginner and advanced to get up close with marine life in a lovely part of the region renowned for its high populations of sea turtles, dolphins and even dugongs. 

Join your friendly crew and hop aboard a luxurious catamaran as you're taken across the scenic stretch of water to Moreton Island, and once there you'll have all diving equipment included to take advantage of the water's many offerings.

**Highlights**  

-   Full use of the Tangalooma Island Resort’s facilities
-   Scuba Diving around the Tangalooma Wrecks
-   Return luxury catamaran transfers
-   Suitable for Intro or Certified divers
-   Free Locker Hire at Tangatours or Watersports
-   Divers both beginner and advanced

properties.name: Moreton Island Wildlife and Wreck Snorkell Cruises
properties.description:
View some of QLD's best marine life up close with this dolphin cruise headed for the Moreton Bay Marine Park and see dolphins, turtles, dugongs and more. 

Access the tour via your own self-drive and then head out on the waters to the spectacular Moreton Bay Marine Park; a wildlife-rich area off the coast of Brisbane home to over 700 Bottlenose dolphins. On this cruise, you will have the opportunity to find these playful and intelligent creatures up close on our catamaran while learning about their habitat, diet, behaviour and other interesting facts. 

Cruise across the scenic waters, enjoying morning tea before arriving at the island.

**Highlights**  

-   Visit iconic Moreton Island
-   Swimming and snorkelling
-   See colourful sub-tropical fish
-   See the Tangalooma Wrecks
-   Enjoy a delicious tropical lunch
-   Transfers from Brisbane or Gold Coast available

properties.name: Kgari Explorer Day Tour from Hervey Bay
properties.description:
Do Fraser in one fun-filled day with an experienced local guide and see the best the island has to offer.

Take a swim in the crystal clear waters of Lake McKenzie or just relax on its dazzling white beaches. Explore Central Station, a former forestry camp with huge satinay, scribbly gum, brush box and kauri trees. Walk along the banks of Wanggoolba Creek which flows gently and silently through lush rainforest. Travel up famous Seventy-Five Mile Beach to see the coloured sands of the Pinnacles and the wreck of the cruise ship Maheno. 
Stop for a swim in Eli Creek as it flows swiftly through the dunes out to sea. Relax and enjoy a hot and cold buffet lunch at Eurong Beach Resort.

**Highlights** 

- Full-day guided Fraser Island 4WD tour
- Delicious lunch at Eurong Beach Resort
- Courtesy pick up from Hervey Bay accommodation
- Enjoy a photo stop at the Maheno Shipwreck
- Relax with a swim at the iconic Lake McKenzie
- Learn the Dreamtime story of The Pinnacles Coloured Sands

properties.name: Great Barrier Reef Snorkel and Dive Cruise
properties.description:
Experience the beautiful Great Barrier Reef with a snorkel and dive cruise departing Port Douglas. Aboard a luxurious, stylish and comfortable catamaran, you'll venture out from the mainland to one of the best reefs in the region, Agincourt Reef. 

This reef is regarded as one of the best and most significant sites in the entire Great Barrier Reef and with this day cruise you'll be able to head below the surface and explore one of them for yourself.

**Highlights**  

-   Full day Great Barrier Reef experience
-   Visit 3 spectacular sites at Agincourt Reef
-   Interpretive reef talk
-   Guided snorkelling tour
-   Morning & afternoon tea
-   Delicious tropical buffet lunch

properties.name: Daintree River Cruise
properties.description:
Witness the wonders of the spectacular Daintree Rainforest from its very heart with a Daintree Rainforest cruise! Over the course of an hour, gently cruise along the Daintree River on an informative wildlife focused experience that will highlight all the various animal and plant life of this fragile and beautiful tropical ecosystem. 

Keep an eye out for rare birds, have your camera ready for seeing crocodiles in their native habitat and much, much more.

Highlights: 

- 1 hour Daintree River cruise
- Experienced Local Guides
- Located at a private boutique location
- Nature walk to private jetty in a Conservation Park
- Experience Nature
- Small personalised groups, make for a more memorable experience

properties.name: Bundaberg Rum Distillery Tours
properties.description:
Go behind the scenes of the Bundaberg Rum Distillery and then sit down with 2 expert distillers to mix your very own rum blend direct from the barrel! 

The blend your own rum experience gives visitors the chance to learn the history behind the iconic Australian spirit brand and see first hand how the rum is produced. 

First, you will join a 1 hour guided tour to view the giant Molasses wells and understand each step of the process from distilling, fermentation and finally the ageing process. After the tour, join expert rum guides to learn the art of tasting rum direct from the barrel.

**Highlights**  

-   Learn about the distillation & fermentation processes
-   Guided Tour into the heart of Bundaberg Rum
-   Interactive Museum Experience
-   2 bottles with your individual blend & name on the front
-   Exclusive hands-on Blend Your Own Rum Experience
-   2 samples of top shelf rums

properties.name: Birdworld Kuranda
properties.description:
Visit Australia's true "home of the birds" at Birdworld Kuranda in QLD's tropical north just 30 minutes' drive from Cairns and 1 hour from Port Douglas for a look at one of the most diverse collections of bird life in the world! 

This interactive, family oriented "bird zoo" located in one of the most popular rainforest areas of Queensland is a must-do for animal lovers visiting the region. With over 75 species of exotic birds from both Australia and abroad. 

Highlights:

- Over 75 species of birds
- Lush rainforest environment
- Hand-feed various birds
- Brilliant Amazonian macaws
- Endangered cassowaries
- Lorikeets, Galahs & Cockatoos

properties.name: Rainforestation Nature Park
properties.description:
Tropical North Queensland's Rainforestation Nature Park is an award-winning attraction allowing visitors to experience Indigenous culture, see native Australian wildlife and explore World Heritage Listed rainforest all in the one place. 

The Park is home to three main attractions - Army Duck Rainforest Tours, Pamagirri Aboriginal Experience and Koala and Wildlife Park - that are all available for visitors to explore with this great package. 

**Highlights**  
-   Get up close and personal with animals
-   45 minute Army Duck Rainforest Tour
-   Pamagirri Aboriginal Experience
-   Crocodile & Koala Photos (extra cost)
-   Pamagirri Rainforest Walkabout
-   Koala & Wildlife Park

properties.name: Tamborine Mountain Rainforest Skywalk
properties.description:
Explore the Gold Coast's Tamborine Mountain with the scenic Rainforest Skywalk. Journey through the emerald green rainforest, the Skywalk will take you from the Rainforest Eco Gallery and on a scenic and adventurous journey through the middle and upper canopies of the rainforest. 

The Skywalk walkway is a stable, high-tech steel structure that takes visitors through the canopies safely and securely while providing spectacular views of the surrounding Hinterland region.

Highlights:

- 1.5km Rainforest Skywalk
- Spectacular Gold Coast hinterland
- Walk takes approximately 45 minutes
- Many points of interest
- Informative information signs along the way
- Set in a magical 30 acres of privately owned rainforest

properties.name: Lone Pine Koala Sanctuary with Return Scenic Cruise
properties.description: Offering a convenient departure point right from the heart of the city, this popular Brisbane River Cruise has been taking visitors to the popular Lone Pine Koala Sanctuary for over 70 years. There is no better way to travel to the largest Koala sanctuary in the world than with a comfortable boat ride along the Brisbane River. It's the perfect way to get up close and see eye to eye with Australia's huge range of native creatures while also enjoying the many sights and sounds of Brisbane's most attractive waterfront suburbs which are accessible only by boat. **Highlights** - Entry to Lone Pine Koala Sanctuary - Modern river boat cruise - See Brisbane's riverfront highlights - Entertaining & informative commentary - Brisbane's best animal attraction - 3 hours to explore the sanctuary

properties.name: Draculas Cabaret Dinner and Show
properties.description:
Book your tickets to Dracula's Gold Coast here to experience all the fun and mayhem in their latest show, 'Sanctuary'! Spend the night being entertained by a devilishly talented cast of performers keeping you entertained throughout the night. 

This energetic after dark experience will fill the room with laughter and applause as the Dracula's Gold Coast cast tease and entertain with their singing, dancing, burlesque, magic and aerial performances.

Highlights:

- Gold Coast's best night out
- Comedy and live performances
- Burlesque, music and acrobatic dance
- Delicious 3 course dinner
- Located in Broadbeach
- A Reserve (VIP) option available

properties.name: Sea World
properties.description:
Sea World is the premier marine animal park on the Gold Coast, Queensland, Australia.

Sea World Gold Coast attractions have something for the whole family. Amazing animals, exciting theme park rides and kids shows and entertainment.

Discover a world of fun and adventure with exciting rides, unforgettable shows and presentations and beautiful marine life

properties.name: Currumbin Wildlife Sanctuary
properties.description:
Currumbin Wildlife Sanctuary on the Gold Coast has long been one of the most popular attractions in south-east Queensland, and it isn't hard to see why. 

Currumbin Sanctuary offers one of the best value days out for families and individuals alike. Get up close with a ton of the best and cutest native Aussie and exotic wildlife - All your animal favourites are here; you can cuddle up to and have your photo taken with a koala, get up close with crocodiles, hand-feed the many friendly kangaroos and much, much more.

Highlights: 

- Cheapest entry tickets online
- The Gold Coast's best wildlife park
- Visit a genuine working wildlife hospital
- 10% off food and beverages in-park
- 10% off retail purchases in-park
- Feed and interact with Kangaroos

properties.name: 1 Day Daintree Rainforest Cape Tribulation and Bloomfield Track Tour
properties.description:
Explore the wonders of two of tropical north QLD's best highlights - the Daintree Rainforest and Cape Tribulation - with an amazing off road 4WD and scenic boat tour! Combining stunning scenery with an in-depth look at the region's abundant flora and fauna.

Highlights: 

- Daintree River Cruise
- Cape Tribulation Beach
- World Heritage Listed Rainforest
- Small personalised group
- Custom built 4WD's
- Gourmet BBQ Lunch

properties.name: Barron River White Water Rafting
properties.description:
The Cairns area's popular Barron River is a great venue to get out on the water and take part in a white water rafting adventure! This Barron River half day white water rafting tour - that includes all necessary rafting equipment - offers 2 hours of pure rafting fun, on a course that offers the intermediate challenge of Grade 3 rapids.

Highlights:

- Beautiful Barron Gorge National Park
- 2 hours White Water Rafting
- All equipment included
- Training and guides included
- Stunning rainforest scenery
- Up to grade 3 rapids

properties.name: Kuranda Riverboat Cruise
properties.description:
Cruise around part of the World's most ancient tropical rainforest with Kuranda Riverboat's scenic and informative water adventure. Aboard this covered open-air vessel, you'll be taken on a journey on part of the Barron River in Kuranda to spot some of its local inhabitants and see the true beauty that Tropical North Queensland is renowned for. 

The Barron River is home to a range of native Australian animals including freshwater crocodiles, turtles, snakes, water dragons and fish as well as the hundreds of tropical bird species that fly around the region.

Highlights:

- Learn the history of Kuranda
- 45 minute rainforest cruise
- The world's most ancient tropical rainforest
- Suitable for all ages
- Departs 5 times daily
- Spot freshwater (estuarine) crocodiles

properties.name: Cairns Jet Boat Ride
properties.description:
Grab your life jacket and strap yourself in for some high-speed fun in Cairns on this 35 minute jet boat adventure that combines thrills and sightseeing in the one enjoyable experience! 

On this Cairns jet boating ride, you'll join the friendly and fun-spirited crew aboard 'Bad Fishy', a turbo-charged jet boat, and head out on the water to perform a range of tricks and turns such as spins, slides, power-brakes and even the occasional 360.

Highlights: 

- Thrilling 35 minute jet boat ride
- Combines thrills with sightseeing
- Awesome twists, turns & spins
- It's wet and wild
- Loads of fun
- Departs from the Cairns Marina

properties.name: Skypark Cairns Bungy Jumping & Giant Swing
properties.description:
This adrenaline pumping experience includes both a Bungy Jump and Giant Swing - two essential Cairns experiences in a single great value package! 

The ultimate combo for thrill seekers visiting the Cairns region, you'll head to the famed Cairns bungy tower within lush rainforest and join the friendly, supportive hosts to check two items off the bucket list.

Highlights: 

- Two essential thrill experiences
- Bungy jumping from 50m high
- Minjin Swing at up to 120km/h
- The only Bungy Tower in Australia
- World only 16 style jump menu

properties.name: Cairns Aquarium
properties.description:
Spend the day exploring the world above and below the water with a visit to the state of the art Cairns Aquarium. 

This must-visit Cairns attraction is full of fun and adventure for all ages to enjoy, Cairns Aquarium will give you a look into the animals that live in both the rainforests and the oceans of Far North Queensland. 

**Highlights**  

-   11 amazing ecosystems to explore
-   Discover over 72 different habitats
-   Over 16,000 aquatic animals
-   Located in the heart of Cairns
-   Open daily 10am - 3pm (last entry 2pm)
-   Touch Tanks with sea stars, sea cucumbers & others

properties.name: Great Barrier Reef Cruise to Reef Magic Pontoon
properties.description:
Discover the many wonders and colours of the Great Barrier Reef with this great value Cairns Reef Tour to popular activity Reef Magic pontoon! The tour departs out of Cairns on a safe and secure catamaran, taking you out to Reef Magic Cruises' exclusive all-weather Reef Magic platform. Here, dive into a stunning coral reef location and discover the diverse marine life. The breathtaking location is a truly once in a lifetime experience that includes snorkelling in a sheltered coral lagoon, scuba diving, and/or a guided Snorkel Safari by an esteemed Marine Biologist. No matter your fitness and experience levels, the Cairns Reef Tour will ensure you make the most of your time out at sea.

The cruise includes all snorkelling equipment and provides a full hot and cold buffet lunch, ensuring that you can discover the reef stress-free. Lay back and enjoy the sunshine on the top deck, or hang out in the underwater observatory and view the rich marine life. The Great Barrier Reef is one of Australia's most prized natural possessions and boasts as one of the seven wonders of the natural world. Book today for an experience you will hold close to your heart for a lifetime.

properties.name: Great Barrier Reef Cruises Snorkelling and Diving
properties.description:
Discover a world of beauty, vibrant coral gardens and diverse marine life when you experience the Outer Barrier Reef on this Quicksilver Port Douglas reef tour. 

Jump aboard the high-speed wave-piercing catamaran and cruise in air-conditioned comfort to the world-famous Agincourt Reef known for its stunning coral formations, colourful marine life and underwater visibility.

Highlights: 

- 6 hour reef cruise tour
- Delicious tropical buffet lunch
- Semi-submersible reef viewing
- Snorkelling equipment included
- Underwater observatory
- Marine biologist presentation

properties.name: Ocean Freedom Great Barrier Reef Tour
properties.description:
Cruise in style and speed to the Great Barrier Reef, providing you with a first class way to experience this natural paradise.

Enjoy personalized snorkelling, certified and introductory diving and a glass bottom boat tour, with friendly, professional crew. This 5 star luxury cruiser visits 2 great destinations – the crystal clear, shallow waters and surrounding reef of Upolu Cay and "Wonder Wall" on the outer edge of Upolu Reef . Explore the wonders of the Great Barrier Reef with us, for an unforgettable day in paradise.

PLEASE NOTE: A compulsory $20pp Environmental Management Charge is payable on board the vessel.

properties.name: Fitzroy Island Adventures
properties.description:
For the quickest and most effective way to get to the beautiful, unspoiled Fitzroy Island, this option includes ferry transfers from Cairns that is not only an efficient way to get "from A to B" but makes for a spectacular tour in itself! 

Heading out from the Cairns Marina, you'll board a comfortable vessel and cruise out across the pristine reef waters towards the wonderful shores of Fitzroy Island on a journey that takes roughly 45 minutes to Fitzroy Island where the real fun starts!

Highlights:

- 45 minute return ferry to Fitzroy Island
- Up to 6 hours to explore Fitzroy Island
- Snorkel with clownfish and sea turtles
- Optional activities once on the island
- Enjoy walks through the rainforest
- Visit the Turtle Rehabilitation Centre

properties.name: Cape Tribulation and Daintree Rainforest Tour
properties.description:
Cape Tribulation in Tropical North Queensland lays claim to the world's best beaches and the oldest surviving rainforest, The Daintree. This budget-friendly day tour from Cairns covers two world heritage sites in one spectacular day. 

Enjoy a day in paradise with ample free time to explore Mossman Gorge, take a walk on the beach and enjoy a meal at the Cape Tribulation Beach House.

Transfers are available from Cairns or Port Douglas.

Highlights: 

- Full Day Cape Tribultion & Daintree Rainforest Tour
- Local tea and beach walk
- Marrdja Boardwalk
- Welcome to Country & Smoking Ceremony at Mossman Gorge
- Alexandra Range Lookout
- Port Douglas

properties.name: Moreton Island Day Tour (ex Brisbane)
properties.description:
Get an island escape from Brisbane on this great value day tour to Moreton Island just off the coast where you'll see marine life as you snorkel from this island paradise near QLD's capital. 

This popular South East QLD getaway spot is teeming with fish as well as its iconic Tangalooma Shipwrecks which provide some great snorkelling opportunities just off shore, and on this day tour, you'll be taken from your Brisbane accommodation to explore its beauty. 
Cruise across the waters of lovely Moreton Bay - keeping an eye out for dolphins and other marine creatures along the way - on board a spacious and modern vessel with air-conditioning and on-board cafe and bar facilities, and soak in the sunshine.

Highlights: 

- Picnic lunch
- Moreton Island full day tour
- Snorkeling, kayaking and sand boarding
- Travel the rugged 4WD tracks
- Snorkel around the ship wrecks
- Have close-up animal encounters

properties.name: Yongala Wreck Dive Trip from Townsville and Magnetic Island
properties.description:
Visit one of the world's 10 best wreck dives with this full day tour from Townsville or Magnetic Island - during which you'll be able to get underwater and see the famed wreck of the SS Yongala up close! 

Situated in the heart of the Great Barrier Reef Marine Park, the SS Yongala sank back in 1911 and has been used as a dive site since 1958, with its untouched nature providing a great haven for a number of spectacular kinds of marine life and coral that make for some wonderful exploration and visual opportunities.

On this full day diving tour you'll join your friendly, experienced diving guides and head out from your choice of either Townsville or Magnetic Island aboard their comfortable vessel headed for the SS Yongala.

**Highlights**  

-   2 dives on the Yongala Wreck
-   Great Barrier Reef Marine Park
-   Great diving on offer
-   Experienced and professional crew
-   See gropers, rays, turtles & more
-   Custom built dive vessel

properties.name: Kgari Fraser Island 2 Day Tour From Rainbow Beach
properties.description:
Come explore this island paradise on an escorted 2 Day Fraser Island 4WD Adventure from Rainbow Beach with meals, transport and a night’s accommodation at Eurong Beach Resort included.

Over the course of two days you’ll see the iconic Lake Mckenzie and Lake Wabby freshwater lakes, recline in a natural jacuzzi at the Champagne Pools, wander through World Heritage Listed rainforest at Central Station, hike across a sand blow and look out for wildlife at Indian Head.

Travelling in custom-built 4WD coaches, this comprehensive 2 Day Tour is the best way to experience the highlights of Fraser Island in two days. Book your spot online here!

properties.name: Sea Life Sunshine Coast
properties.description:
One of the most popular attractions on the Sunshine Coast for many years, SEA LIFE Sunshine Coast is Queensland's largest aquarium and oceanarium with one of the hugest and most diverse arrays of marine life - both above and under the water - on display in Australia! 

Highlights: 

- FREE digital photo pass with 8 x digital photos (valued at $26) 
- Skip the queues with express mobile ticket entry 
- Multiple themed zones 
- Conveniently located in the heart of Mooloolaba 
- Thousands of marine & freshwater animals 
- Queensland's largest aquarium

properties.name: Noosa Jetboat Adventure Tour
properties.description:
The Oceanrider Adventure Tour is a faster-paced tour that starts at the Noosa Marina with a cruise down the Noosa River and crossing the Noosa Bar, where the river meets the sea at Laguna Bay. You will experience tighter turns and the manoeuvring capabilities of the Gemini RiB that is Oceanrider while encountering and negotiating ocean swells and waves.

Highlights:

- Fast-paced tour
- Scenic views of the Noosa coast
- Fun & laughter with your mates
- Experience tighter turns
- Manoeuvring capabilities
- Sightings of dolphins and whales (in season)

properties.name: Hervey Bay Turtle Discovery Marine Tours
properties.description:
Cruise the clear waters of the Great Sandy Strait near Hervey Bay for a marine eco tour discovering turtles, dolphins, sea birds and even dugongs! This leisurely day cruise travels in one of Australia’s largest glass bottom boats so you are guaranteed the best views of marine life and the coral gardens underwater and around the vessel. 

Snorkelling equipment is provided so feel free to jump in the water to swim and snorkel amongst the marine life. See local landmarks such as Round Island and Pelican banks while listening to informative commentary about the local Aboriginal Butchulla people. A healthy lunch, bottled water and tea and coffee is included in the marine eco tour. Cruises depart daily at 10.30am from Urangan and return at 3pm.

**Highlights**  

-   Hervey Bay half-day eco tour
-   Cruise the Great Sandy Straits in a glass-bottom boat
-   Delicious tropical lunch
-   Spot dolphins, turtles and dugongs
-   Swim & snorkel in the calm, crystal clear waters
-   Listen to dreamtime stories from a local Indigenous guide

properties.name: Great Barrier Reef Cruise from Mission Beach
properties.description:
Explore the underwater world of the Great Barrier Reef during this Outer Reef tour on board the ' MV Reef Goddess', a beautiful custom built snorkel and dive vessel. 

The world-famous Great Barrier Reef is Queensland's gem and a natural attraction you must visit at least once, thanks to this day cruise from Mission Beach, you can spend the entire day exploring the vibrant coral reefs, coming face-to-face with curious marine life and relaxing on the deck while floating in paradise. 


Highlights: 

- A full day outer Great Barrier Reef experience 
- Free snorkel briefing and tuition 
- Visit 2 outer reef locations 
- Delicious BBQ lunch with fresh prawns, salads and tropical fruit 
- Fun filled, educational experience

properties.name: Southern Great Barrier Reef Cruise - Lady Musgrave Island
properties.description:
Experience one of the Seven Wonders of the World with a day cruise to Lady Musgrave Island in the Southern Great Barrier Reef from the Town of 1770. 

Join this day cruise and travel on a high speed catamaran for 90 minutes to enjoy 5 hours at the only coral cay island in the Great Barrier Reef that is surrounded by a protected and wildlife rich reef lagoon. 

This is the perfect playground for adventurers with complimentary snorkel hire equipment, guided island walks and glass bottom boat rides over the coral reef gardens and marine life all included. The pristine waters of Lady Musgrave Island are a haven for marine life and sightings of manta rays, tropical fish and turtles are almost guaranteed here as you swim or snorkel the lagoon. 

Highlights: 

- Snorkel on the Southern Great Barrier Reef with stunning marine life including turtles, manta rays, reef fish and stunning corals 
- Enjoy a guided island nature walk with a local tour guide 
- Take in more of the coral lagoon on a glass bottom boat tour 
- Swim in the pristine clear aqua blue waters of Lady Musgrave Island 
- Morning tea, afternoon tea and a delicious buffet lunch included

properties.name: Great Barrier Reef Dive and Snorkel Cruise
properties.description:
Explore the best of the Great Barrier Reef both in & above the water with this great value full day cruise package from Cairns, visiting several great Outer Reef sites throughout the course of the day! 

Featuring a comprehensive tour itinerary, you'll get to see all the vivid, colourful, World Heritage beauty of the Great Barrier Reef, and have the chance to view it up close for yourself with included use of all the state-of-the-art snorkel and scuba equipment included in the price. 

Highlights

- Return fast catamaran cruise
- 3 hours on the Outer Reef
- Semi-submersible reef viewing tour
- Morning tea, lunch & afternoon tea
- Multi-level reef activity platform
- Underwater observatory

properties.name: Tasman Venture Whale Watching Hervey Bay
properties.description:
For Hervey Bay's ultimate whale watching and Fraser Island experience, cruise aboard the Tasman Venture. 

Summer Remote Fraser Island Tour Inclusions:- FREE transfers from accommodation places in Hervey Bay.

Includes activities: Kayaking, SUP, Tube Riding, Snorkelling and Guided Walks - Morning tea - BBQ Lunch - Afternoon tea - Air-conditioned cabin - Underwater viewing windows - Expert commentary 

Experience the trip of a lifetime aboard the luxurious and fast 20 metre catamaran, Tasman Venture. 

Let the humpback whales amaze you with their close encounters, magical songs through the hydrophone, spectacular breaching and see them swim through the underwater viewing windows. 

Experience the whales even closer from the specifically designed viewing platform which takes you right to the waters edge. Their friendly and accredited staff will provide you the best experience, with expert commentary about the whales, dolphins, birds and other wildlife, (multi-lingual staff onboard and information available in five languages).

properties.name: Low Isles Cruise
properties.description:
Looking to visit the Low Isles on the Great Barrier Reef? This half day cruise departing from Port Douglas is a great way for those short on time to visit the Great Barrier Reef. After a picturesque 30 minute cruise, be transported to the crystal clear waters of the Low Isles for a guided snorkel tour and free time to explore the unique island. 

You will have two and a half hours to snorkel this calm water reef lagoon and view over 150 varieties of coral and tropical fish that can be found here. 

This tour is also perfect for non-swimmers who can take in views of the coral reef from a glass bottom boat or dry land. You may also wish to wander the grounds of the island to view the historic lighthouse, weather station and a variety of bird life.

**Highlights:**
-   Morning cruise to Low Isles
-   2.5hrs to explore Low Isles
-   Snorkel in the calm lagoon
-   Glass bottom boat tour
-   All snorkelling equipment supplied
-   Muffins, fruit, tea & coffee included

properties.name: Great Barrier Reef Cruise to Hardy Reef Pontoon
properties.description:
Visit one of the Whitsunday region's most spectacular Great Barrier Reef sites on this great value day tour departing from Airlie Beach. 

Witness the Great Barrier Reef at its best with a cruise to the Outer Reef, where both the water quality and incredible marine life are at their most magnificent! Departing from Airlie Beach, on this Outer Reef cruise you'll board one of the region's premier vessels and enjoy a morning tea and the stunning views as you cruise through the Whitsunday Islands and on to the outer Great Barrier Reef.

**highlights:**
-   Underwater Observatory
-   All snorkelling equipment provided
-   Full Day Outer Great Barrier Reef Experience
-   Reefworld Pontoon
-   Semi-submarine guided tour
-   Delicious gourmet lunch pack included

properties.name: Whitehaven Beach Ocean Rafting
properties.description:
Whitehaven Xpress is positioned as "The Ultimate Whitehaven Beach Experience" by offering more time at Whitehaven Beach Hill Inlet than any other Airlie Beach Tour. 

The Point of Difference for this day tour is the Aussie BBQ Lunch served on Whitehaven Beach (opposed to on the boat).The staff to guest ratio is higher than most tours offering a more personalised experience. 

Maximum capacity is 47 passengers however she usually carries 37. Commissioned specifically for the Whitsundays, the MV Lindeman Pacifici s a 15M Fiberglass constructed mono-hull vessel powered by two motors combining for over 900 horse power. 

She has Indoor, Outdoor and Upstairs seating As Well As toilets and a licensed bar. Whitehaven Xpress is now operated by the owners Jill Dan. Whitehaven Xpress is the only pioneering day tour which is still Owner Operated. Est 1989.

properties.name: Iconic Whitsunday Adventures
properties.description:
Airlie Beach's favourite and original sunset cruise. Our flat pontoon boat offers easy access to move around, plenty of seating, a well-stocked bar, a smoking area and a toilet on board. 

Our friendly staff will welcome you aboard for a 2 hour sunset cruise around Airlie Beach and Pioneer Bay, while you enjoy a platter of nibbles, a complimentary glass of bubbly on arrival, the afternoon sun, a beautiful sunset, and the lights of Airlie Beach at night. Airlie Beach's best sunset cruise, suitable for all ages. Cruise the Whitsundays on board Sundowner and view Airlie Beach from a different perspective. 

Enjoy an amazing sunset cruise where the Whitsunday Islands provide the perfect backdrop, then watch Airlie Beach light up at night as they cruise back to port.

properties.name: Lone Pine Koala Sanctury Scenic Cruise
properties.description:
Brisbane's only river cruise to the world famous Lone Pine Koala Sanctuary.

The Koala and River Cruise is a memorable journey on the Brisbane River to the renowned Lone Pine Koala Sanctuary and has been taking visitors for over 70 years. Your river cruise takes you from the bustling waterfront of Southbank to the lush parklands of Lone Pine, with the chance to see iconic sights and historic landscapes as you glide along the water, listening to an entertaining and informative commentary. 

At the Lone Pine Koala Sanctuary you can cuddle koalas, feed kangaroos, and watch platypus, sheepdogs and birds of prey in action. Animal lovers will not want to miss this experience!

properties.name: AquaDuck
properties.description: Experience the Gold Coast on our amphibious ‘Duck. It’s a city tour and river cruise all in one.

properties.name: Cairns Aquarium
properties.description:
As the only aquarium in the world dedicated exclusively to the habitats and species of tropical North Queensland, the Cairns Aquarium connects visitors with the natural wonders of The Great Barrier Reef, The Wet Tropics, The Gulf Savannah and Cape York regions. 

With over 16,000 animals and unique opportunities to move up close to some of the world's most fascinating, elusive or deadly creatures, every visit is unforgettable.

properties.name: Coomera Holiday Village
properties.description:
Coomera Village Holiday Park is your ideal base for an unforgettable holiday experience. Our spacious and pet-friendly caravan park offers a variety of affordable accommodation options, perfect for families, couples, and groups seeking an escape close to nature.


Coomera Village Holiday Park boasts an unbeatable location, placing you just minutes away from world-famous theme parks like Dreamworld, WhiteWater World, and Movie World. Experience the thrills and spills of these iconic attractions, creating memories that will last a lifetime.

properties.name: Lone Pine Koala Sanctuary
properties.description:
Take a trip to the Lone Pine Koala Sanctuary, Brisbane's premier tourist attraction, where you'll get to experience hands-on interaction with all kinds of fascinating Australian animals. You can cuddle with koalas, hand-feed kangaroos and encounter a wide variety of Aussie wildlife just 50 minutes from the Gold Coast.

Take some time to appreciate and learn the stories of the animals, helping you develop a newfound appreciation for the natural world and a desire to do your part in protecting it. You can even attend a talk about native wildlife and habitats, where you'll learn about the challenges facing these animals and leave feeling inspired to make small, positive changes in your daily life to help protect your own native wildlife and habitats.

**Highlights:**

 -  The world's largest koala sanctuary
-   Over 100 koalas and over 70 native species
-   Cuddle a koala (extra cost)
-   Hand-feed kangaroos and emus
-   See the daily raptor and sheep dog shows
-   Experience touching a koala, snake or dingo (extra cost)

properties.name: Whitehaven Beach and Hamilton Island Tour with Lunch
properties.description:
Explore two must-visit destinations in the Whitsunday Islands with our day cruise. Begin your day at Whitehaven Beach, where you'll have 2 hours of free time to swim in crystal blue waters, stroll along the pristine white silica sand, or enjoy beach activities. 

Afterward, savor a delicious lunch before heading to Hamilton Island in the afternoon. On Hamilton Island, relish a pub-style lunch, access the shuttle bus for island exploration, and take advantage of the luxurious resort pools or Catseye Beach. 

Conclude your day with a return to the Port of Airlie after an unforgettable exploration of the Whitsundays. Book your Whitehaven Beach and Hamilton Island day cruise online today to check off two essential Whitsunday Islands from your bucket list.

**Highlights:** 
- Whitehaven Beach & Hamilton Island Full Day Tour 
- 2 hours on Whitehaven Beach 
- Lunch overlooking Hamilton Island Marina 
- Morning tea included 
- Full use of shuttle bus and pool areas 
- 2 of Australia's most loved destinations

properties.name: Australian Outback Spectacular Heartland Dinner & Show
properties.description:
Australia's Outback Spectacular presents their new show, Heartland. Come along and witness a heart warming and immersive arena show with a three course meal and beverages, incredible special effects, inspiring animal performances and a star studded cast.

Set in the Australian Outback Spectacular's iconic red barn, be transported to the outback with an all new arena show featuring a cast of talented Australian actors and the latest technology that depicts farm life during a severe drought. Follow the true story of farmers Reg and Marge who are struggling to keep their farm going after 5 years without rain. The story depicts the real struggles of Australian farmers and life in the outback as told through humour, quirky characters and friendship set to the soundtrack of popular Australian country music. 

Highlights include:
- Australian Dinner & Show
- 3 course dinner + drinks during the show
- FREE stockman's hat
- Leading Stunt Riders, Stockmen & Women
- Classic Australian entertainment
- Pre-Show Entertainment

properties.name: Great Barrier Reef Scenic Helicopter Flight
properties.description:
Take off from Cairns city and experience the sheer size and beauty of the Great Barrier Reef on this spectacular 30 minute scenic helicopter flight! See this incredible Natural Wonder of the World and all of its incredible colours, corals and marine life from an angle few get to experience. It's a panorama that is truly stunning, and over the course of the 30 minute flight you'll fly over beautiful reef islands, pristine turquoise waters and untouched coral cays along the way. You will soar over local icon Green Island, gaze directly down into the marine-life-filled Arlington Reef, pass over Vlasoff and Upolu Sand Cays and much, much more.

Highlights:
- 30 Minute Scenic Helicopter Flight
- Green Island
- Arlington Reef
- Vlasoff Sand Cay
- Upolu Sand Cay
- Cairns hotel transfers included

properties.name: Whale Watching Cruise from Surfers Paradise
properties.description:
See these incredibly impressive - yet truly gentle - ocean giants between the months of June and November as they frolic and play in the warm seas just off the shore of one of Australia's most popular tourist cities.

On this whale watching tour, you'll join one of the state's most experienced and knowledgeable whale watching companies for a cruise past the houses of the rich and famous before coming up close with the whales themselves. Whale Watching Cruises are 3.5 hours in duration and depart at 9am and 2pm.

**Highlights:**
- Only Whale Watching Cruise from Surfers Paradise
- Marvel at humpback whales up close
- 3.5 hour whale watch cruise
- Uncrowded whale watch experience
- See the homes of the Gold Coast's rich & famous
- Knowledgeable crew

properties.name: Gold Coast Scenic Cruise
properties.description:
Join us on the lovely waters of the Gold Coast of an evening for a spectacular dinner cruise. Departing from Sea World Terminal at 7pm, you’ll be able to climb on board our large, newly-refurbished sightseeing vessel and soak in the great atmosphere of the city lights while enjoying a cold drink from the fully licensed bar and a delicious dinner comprising of fresh prawns fro local Gold Coast trawlers plus a hot selection and desserts.

All whilst taking in the spectacular city lights of the Surfers Paradise skyline. Spend your evening being entertained by live, on board entertainment and by relaxing on our rooftop lounge.

HIghlights: 

- Live on board entertainment
- 2.5 hour sightseeing dinner cruise
- Fresh prawns from local Gold Coast trawlers
- Relax on the rooftop lounge
- Departs from Sea World Terminal
- See famous local landmarks such as Sea World, Versace & more

properties.name: BIG4 Adventure Whitsunday Resort
properties.description: Owned and operated by the McKinnon family, BIG4 Adventure Whitsunday Resort has developed an enviable reputation as one of the state's leading resort holiday parks. The resort offers an atmosphere that is genuinely warm, friendly, relaxed and welcoming with an incredibly dedicated team of staff who share our family's passion and vision.

properties.name: Tully Memorial Park
properties.description: This riverside park offers free overnight camping to self-contained vehicles only. The sites are large and grassy with scenic views. There are toilet facilities, picnic tables, BBQs and rubbish bins. The limit of 3 nights out of every 30 days period applies.

properties.name: BIG4 Maroochy River
properties.description:
If your idea of the perfect park is a relaxed environment, a sense of community and plenty to do (or not do) in the local area, we are the park for you. A stay with us will leave you with fond lasting memories and a great holiday experience. 

We have a range of cabins to choose from and a good range of large campsites that are perfect for big vans, camper trailers and those also with a boat or trailer in tow. All cabins and sites are close to the amenities, the pool, camp kitchen and the BBQ areas.

properties.name: BarraCrab Caravan Park
properties.description:
BarraCrab is a family owned and run caravan park. We have absolute beach frontage and provide travellers with a unique and friendly holiday experience.

If you enjoy relaxing walks along the beach, or good fishing? Simply want to stop and enjoy the view? Visit BarraCrab Caravan Park!

BarraCrab is the perfect place to stop and enjoy a beautiful stretch of the Australian coastline. Ask management for advice on the best fishing spots, or enjoy the massive expanse of Clairview beach on early morning walks.

properties.name: BIG4 Whitsundays Tropical Eco Resort
properties.description:
Welcome to BIG4 Whitsundays Tropical Eco Resort, nestled in 7 acres of lush tropical rainforest. As the gateway to the spectacular Whitsundays, we are only a few minutes drive to the major ports and township of Airlie Beach where you will find a variety of restaurants to suit all budgets and boutique style shops for your shopping “fix”.

BIG4 Whitsundays Tropical Eco Resort, with its team of dedicated and passionate staff share a vision “to create a unique and memorable Eco experience for all of our guests, different to anything our competitors can create”.

Within our park we have a sparkling swimming pool, kids play area and Jumping Pillow. We also have a Ninja Challenge inflatable obstacle course - fun for all ages!! Quad bikes are also available for hire and we offer Kids Club during school holidays.

properties.name: Mareeba Heritage Museum & Visitor Information Centre
properties.description:
The Mareeba Heritage Centre provides a diverse range of information and assistance to tourists traveling throughout the area. The centre has a coffee house, a historical museum for a small admission fee of $5 pp, souvenirs and gifts, stamps and free WIFI.
The centre’s friendly staff and volunteers are local residents with extensive knowledge about the area and are happy to assist.
Recently qualified for the Trip Advisor Certificate of Excellence Hall of Fame the Centre is open seven days a week, from 9am to 4pm Monday-Friday and 8am to 3pm Saturday-Sunday, 362 days of the year with ample parking for both vehicles and caravans.

properties.name: BIG4 Port Douglas Glengarry Holiday Park
properties.description: Situated between the Great Barrier Reef and ancient World Heritage rainforest, Port Douglas is a unique link to the diversity of Australia. Our beautifully landscaped BIG4 holiday park is only 7km from town. Relax, revive and experience the wonderful hospitality of Glengarry by staying in our cabins, villas, caravan sites or camping!

properties.name: Discovery Parks - Airlie Beach
properties.description:
Discovery Parks - Airlie Beach is your gateway to the enchanting white sands of the Whitsunday Islands - set against a tranquil, tropical paradise. Say g'day to all sorts of Australian wildlife, including kangaroos, wallabies, possums, goannas, scrub turkeys and parrots.

This holiday park is the at the centre of all your Whitsundays adventures with cruises, scenic flights, ocean rafting, and day trips easily booked through the front desk. 

From cabins amongst the tall gnarled trees through to pet friendly sites, you'll be daydreaming about your Airlie Beach holiday.

properties.name: Whitsundays Visitor Information Centre
properties.description:
The Whitsundays Visitor Information Centre is here to help you with:

- Local insights and information on The Whitsunday region. 

- All your Whitsunday itinerary needs and book them in one spot.

- Brochures and maps of The Whitsundays and Queensland.

- Large caravan friendly car park. 

It is a great stopping point during your travels. Offering a beautiful Café with fresh coffee and local produce, a small animal park and bird aviary (which is free to enjoy) and indoor air-conditioned children’s play centre. The visitor information centre team can assist you either in person via email, phone or online chat!


## Sensory Audio Guides

properties.name: Alkoomi Adventure Farmstay & Campground
properties.description:
Central Queensland's best working cattle Farmstay. Home of Droughtie the Big Bull. Large powered/unpowered sites. Quiet peaceful surrounds suitable for all ages. 
Low cost camping/ensuite rooms. 
Check-in between 2pm - 6pm.  Please call to make a booking. Hot showers/toilets.
Camp kitchen
Electric & woodfired BBQs 
Paddock to plate Alkoomi beef available 
Free firewood 
Campoven pit
Free animal feeding & vintage wagon ride daily, (4pm May-September 4:30pm October-April, excludes December.
Sunset Shack with panoramic views from the mountains to the ocean. 
Sunset Chuckwagon tours available 
Swimming/fishing
Kayaking/paddle boarding (BYO)
Bicycle tracks
9kms of walking tracks 
Horse riding available for all ages
Motorbike Hire for all ages
UTV farm Tour available

properties.name: BIG4 Caloundra Holiday Park
properties.description:
While located in the heart of Caloundra, the park offers all the amenity of Caloundra and a range of facilities and activities, so you and the kids won't have to leave the park for fun.

From the heated pool and the Jumping Pillow through to the BBQ areas and places to sit back, relax and take in the stunning water views, BIG4 Caloundra is the perfect holiday location.

For a holiday packed full of family fun, you've found the ultimate destination. Ideally situated on the magnificent water views, choose accommodation from luxury cabins or the fun of camping.

With the heated pool, jumping pillow and our fabulous school holiday activities program, the kids will have fun and mum and dad will get to relax all in one of the best holidays parks on the Sunshine Coast.
We are a family business that takes pride in delivering a great customer experience with the best and cleanest amenities, facilities, and accommodation options. From our General Manager through to housekeepers, customer service, and grounds staff our single-driven mission is to delight and deliver you and your family a great holiday experience.

properties.name: Noosa Sea Scout
properties.description:
Our shady campground is situated in Noosaville.  Our function is primarily the Noosa Sea Scout Group. However we have a popular and spacious campground and bunkhouse which we make available to groups, families, travelers and community organisations at certain times.
We are not a commercial business; all profits improve the onsite facilities.
We are a quiet, family-friendly campground, not suitable for parties, or unruly behaviour.
Generally, we are open to the public from Friday to Monday inclusive during term-time and during Queensland school holidays
We reserve the right to close without notice due to weather, health and safety reasons or other unforeseen circumstances.

properties.name: Tasman Holiday Parks - South Mission Beach
properties.description:
Imagine 14 kilometres of white sandy beaches backing onto World Heritage-listed tropical rainforest where cassowaries roam. This is South Mission Beach.

Located just two hours from Cairns, on the Cassowary Coast, this is the closest access to the world-renowned Great Barrier Reef.

A magical place between the coast and the rainforest, South Mission is a world of its own. Swim in beautiful tropical waters under the coconut palms that stretch out into the ocean. Islands, coral reefs, tropical rainforests, rare animals including the endangered Cassowaries, and tropical fruits complete the picture.

Escape the southern winter months or holiday all year round. Hire a villa or cabin, park the van or pitch a tent. Life doesn't get any better!

properties.name: BIG4 Mackay Blacks Beach Holiday Park
properties.description: BIG4 Mackay Blacks Beach Holiday Park is perfectly positioned on absolute beachfront, overlooking the southern islands of the Whitsundays. Set on five beachfront acres, BIG4 Mackay Blacks Beach Holiday Park offers guests modern facilities and services in picturesque surrounds.

properties.name: Cane Village Holiday Park - Bundaberg
properties.description: Our attractive park is set amid beautiful gardens, quiet and secure, and within walking distance to Stockland Shopping Centre, Brothers Sports Club, bowling club, cinema and a bus stop opposite to venture into the CBD just 5km away. Dawn and the team at BIG4 Cane Village Holiday Park look forward to welcoming you.

properties.name: Six Mile Creek Rest Area
properties.description: Small rest area just off the highway with covered picnic tables and flushing toilets.  Some road noise.

properties.name: BIG4 Townsville Gateway Holiday Park
properties.description:
A tranquil holiday park just outside of Townsville in sunny Queensland. Shady native trees and beautiful birdlife provide the perfect setting to help you unwind on your tropical holiday.

Basking in more than 300 days of sunshine each year, Townsville is home to some spectacular natural landscapes and attractions. Explore tropical islands, wetlands, the Great Barrier Reef, rainforests, and beachfront while you laze and enjoy the tropical weather.

BIG4 Townsville Gateway Holiday Park is located just 10 minutes from the CBD and within easy reach of local attractions.

properties.name: Tamborine Mountain Visitor Information Centre
properties.description:
Tamborine Mountain Visitors Information Centre  Is located in Doughty Park, on the corner of Geissmann Drive and Main Street opposite the petrol station. 

The information centre volunteers will be able to advise you on everything that there is to do on Tamborine Mountain, from the beautiful bush walks, where all the waterfalls are, the best places to eat and shop on the mountain. 

The centre also has a large range of local produce to purchase. The volunteers will also be able to advise you upcoming local events, both on Tamborine Mountain and the Scenic Rim.  

![Events banner](https://www.thetourismgroup.com.au/images/AUS_VIC_APP/Events_Banner_for_app.jpg)
[**What's on in the region**](https://www.visitscenicrim.com.au/whats-on/events/)

properties.name: BP Townsville
properties.description:
No tents, no open flames and no pilot lights.

Max stay: 24hrs. Behind a busy BP station, cafe and next to a Bunnings Warehouse. Well established place with lots of vans. Free WiFi, $5 hot showers, toilets are clean, rubbish bins available.

properties.name: Burdekin Gateway Visitor Information Centre
properties.description:
Start your Burdekin adventure at the Burdekin Gateway Visitor Information Centre, conveniently located just off the Bruce Highway on Railway Avenue in Home Hill. As an accredited Visitor Information Centre, you'll find an array of brochures, maps and itineraries to guide your journey.  The friendly and knowledgeable locals are ready to help you explore the region, assisting with travel advice, directions and recommendations on places to eat or refuel, making your visit hassle-free. Enjoy the comfort of free Wi-Fi, air conditioning and a Driver Reviver stop that serves free tea and coffee. With lots of parking space for caravans and motor homes, the Burdekin Gateway Visitor Information Centre is the perfect stop when travelling Queensland. Whilst at the Visitor Information Centre, be sure to check out the S.S. Yongala Dive Virtual Reality Experience, you can experience one of the world's most famous dives and learn the history of the S.S. Yongala that sank off the coast of Alva in 1911 in the comfort of the Centre through top quality VR. The Centre houses part of a historical photo collection featuring the construction of the iconic Burdekin Bridge from 1947 to 1957.

The Centre is situated behind the Home Hill Comfort Stop, which boasts some of the cleanest amenities in Australia, completely free of charge. Facilities include toilets, hot showers, BBQ areas, meal preparation benches, sinks, picnic tables, and a disabled toilet. Parking for self-contained vehicles is available on Railway Avenue, with visitors permitted to stay for a maximum of 48 hours at no cost. During the winter months from April through to September, the Comfort Stop is very popular and it is best to arrive by lunchtime to secure your spot for the night. 

Discover Burdekin

[**Things to do**](https://www.visitburdekin.com.au/things-to-do)

[**Accommodation**](https://www.visitburdekin.com.au/stay)

[**Events & Festivals**](https://www.visitburdekin.com.au/whats)

[**Practical Information**](https://www.visitburdekin.com.au/practical-info/practical-info-1)

properties.name: BIG4 Sandstone Point Holiday Resort
properties.description: On the glistening shores of Pumicestone Passage, a stone’s throw from the iconic Bribie Island is BIG4 Sandstone Point Holiday Resort. Located directly in between Brisbane CBD and the Sunshine Coast, there is plenty to do with magnificent beaches and scenic bushland showcasing the best of South East Queensland escapes.

properties.name: BIG4 Lucinda Wanderers Holiday Park
properties.description: BIG4 Lucinda Wanderers Holiday Park is a nature-lover’s tropical beachside holiday park. The park is located in beautiful Lucinda a coastal town in North Queensland, directly opposite the tip of World Heritage listed Hinchinbrook Island. Take in the stunning palm trees and birds while you unwind and enjoy all the beauty of the tropical North Queensland coast. Whether you're hiking the Thorsborne Trail, fishing the Hinchinbrook Channel or here to lounge by the pool BIG4 Lucinda Wanderers Holiday Park is the perfect place for your Lucinda getaway!

properties.name: Charlotte Plains Station
properties.description:
Charlotte Plains is a family-owned, operated sheep station and campground, near Cunnamulla – Queensland. Our Artesian Hot Springs offer a naturally heated water park for guests wishing to soak in the warm mineral-rich water, while taking in the stunning views of the surrounding landscape.

In addition to the Hot Springs, we offer an authentic Australian outback experience to visitors, combining an insight into sheep station life and occasionally offering guided tours! There is also a spectacular array of birds for birdwatchers and other animals, surrounding the campgrounds.

properties.name: BIG4 Gold Coast Holiday Park
properties.description: BIG4 Gold Coast Holiday Park is located in prime position when looking for Gold Coast tourist parks. It is the nearest caravan park to the Gold Coast Theme Parks with family and pooch friendly accommodation. With a monster Water Park and outdoor pool area, located next to an onsite café, it's the perfect place to base yourself. Accessible options also available

properties.name: Cardwell Van Park
properties.description: Cardwell Van Park offers accommodation in a quiet and peaceful setting with tropical atmosphere.  Cardwell Van Park is an owner operated caravan park and your host Colin Oke will make you feel at home. The park boasts 45 Powered sites and cabin style accommodation, laundry, camp kitchen, town water, T.V. connection to all sites five free to air channels. Large spacious amenities with good size showers. Room for boats to park. Some large drive thru sites are available. The fishermen among you will be pleased to know that Cardwell Van Park is close to all weather boat ramp.

properties.name: Ipswich Visitor Information Centre
properties.description:
# Ipswich Visitor Information Centre

The Ipswich Visitor Information Centre is an award-winning tourist centre and is home to passionate volunteers who have over 1,200 years combined experience living and working in Ipswich. This friendly team of knowledgeable locals is available seven days a week to provide insights into the things to see and do throughout the Ipswich region. Calling in to the Ipswich Visitor Information Centre is a must for travellers wanting to make the most of their stay in Ipswich.

Located in Ipswich's picturesque Queens Park, the Ipswich Visitor Information Centre offers a one stop shop for travel information including maps, brochures and travel planning. Included in a long list of visitor services are a free booking service for accommodation and tours; a great selection of local souvenirs, produce and local arts and crafts; free parking for cars, caravans and coaches; cafe for light refreshments; and free WiFi internet access. There's even a shower for the long-haul travellers.

properties.name: Bundaberg Visitor Information Centre
properties.description:
The Bundaberg Visitor Information Centre is an accredited visitor information centre offering a one stop shop for travel information including maps, brochures and itineraries. Staffed by skilled and knowledgeable locals, the Bundaberg Visitor Information Centre can provide advice on the things to see, things to do and where to eat as well as make bookings for their many fantastic accommodation, tours and attractions. The regional Visitor Information Centres are the key distributor for Mon Repos Turtle Encounter tickets each summer, where you can experience the miracle of life on their shores. Swim with giant marine life on the Southern Great Barrier Reef, indulge in their culinary delights including their iconic and boutique drinks industry or enjoy their stunning hinterlands and beaches. They are located on Avenue Street in the East Bundaberg Tourism Precinct, in close proximity to the Bundaberg Rum Visitor Experience, Bundaberg Brewed Drinks' Barrel, Ohana Cider House and Riverfeast. Come and chat with their friendly staff about your travel plans or make a booking.

properties.name: Mycow Caravan Park and Campground
properties.description:
This newly refurbished caravan park and camp ground is set out on the edge of picturesque Bakers Creek. A landscaped boardwalk extends the length of the water’s edge which leads to a bbq deck, fishing pier and a number breakout grassed fishing areas complete with rod holders. There is a range of both powered and unpowered sites catering for tents, camping trailers, caravans and up to 40 foot motorhomes.
Fast free Wi-Fi throughout the whole park. Air-Conditioned laundromat with TV. Fully equipped camp kitchen with lounge area and all equipment and utensils provided. Fully Self Contained Studio’s, King Single Cabins, Twins Share Rooms, Unpowered Sites, Powered Sites and Drive Through Sites.

properties.name: Brisbane North Rental Village
properties.description:
Brisbane North Rental Village is a great value cabin and caravan park in Brisbane. The park is located in a great position on Gympie Road, Aspley with lots of things nearby. It’s perfect for single people, couples and families with the different accommodation types to suit your budget and needs.

Looking for a cheap place to stay in Brisbane? 

You will love Brisbane North Rental Village, our friendly team and the range of cabin and caravan accommodation options. There are 1 bedroom, 2 bedroom and Studio options and the cabins with ensuite facilities are very popular!

Many sizes of rental caravans and our powered caravan sites all have easy access to well maintained amenities. Arrange an obligation free tour for yourself today.

properties.name: Mackay Isaac Visitor Information Kiosk
properties.description:
# Mackay Isaac Visitor Information Kiosk

The Mackay isaac Visitor Information Kiosk is located outside the Bluewater Lagoon Mackay, assisting the high volume of tourists who visit the City Centre and the Bluewater Lagoon every year. The open counter kiosk allows volunteers to hand out brochures to tourists and provide local information.


## Top 10 Things to do in the Mackay Isaac Region
**1.** Tour and taste what’s on offer at the multi-award-winning  Sarina Sugar Shed.

**2.** Explore the hidden wonders that lay above and below the island waters off the coast of Mackay with a day trip on WildCat Mackay

**3.** Discover historical, creative and educational experiences at the Sarina District Historical Centre and Yukan Art Gallery – all within the Fields of Dreams Parklands

**4.** Snap a selfie with the local wallabies and eastern grey kangaroos when you trip to Cape Hillsborough beach. While you are there you can trek, picnic and explore the astonishing Cape Hillsborough National Park
– the site of rainforests, eucalyptus, mangroves, shorelines and rocky headlands.

**5.** Tick off your ‘Australia big things’ list with a selfie alongside Buffy the big cane toad!

**6.** Drive to the Mackay CBD and take a splash at the Blue Lagoon pools near Pioneer River.

**7.** Explore and relax at many unspoiled seashore locations including Freshwater Point, Coral Point Reef and Grasstree beach.

**8.** Experience Australia’s youngest tropical and cultural oasis just 30 mins north at the MacKay Regional Botanic Gardens

**9.** Take a drive through the Pioneer Valley and visit Finch Hatton Gorge and Eungella National Park.  While you are there make sure to try and spot a platypus up at Broken River.

**10.** View the largest coal export facility in the world from Hay Point terminal lookout.

properties.name: BIG4 Breeze Holiday Parks - Carnarvon Gorge
properties.description:
Set amongst Carnarvon National Park on 100 acres is BIG4 Breeze Holiday Parks - Carnarvon Gorge. It’s the perfect destination to disconnect from the hustle of life and reconnect with nature. Just a five-minute drive from where your Carnarvon Gorge walks begin, Breeze Holiday Parks is the perfect base.

Your nature escape doesn’t stop when you leave the Gorge – the area is home to 173 species of birds, 60 different mammals, 22 species of frogs and 90 reptiles. Even the elusive platypus can be spotted by the keen eye from the banks of the Carnarvon Creek, which wraps itself around the holiday park.

properties.name: Mitchell Explore Centre
properties.description:

Browse our range of unique merchandise and locally made products or relax with a coffee on the deck. properties.name: Flinders Discovery Centre
properties.description:
# Flinders Discovery Centre
 
Your first stop in town should be to pull up at the Flinders Discovery Centre to say gidday to  the friendly local staff that can provide all the local insights and help you plan a local itinerary to suit your interests. There is a comprehensive selection of free local guide books along with regional destination guides and maps. The Centre also stocks a great range of souvenirs, specialising in locally made items, fossils & minerals, and of course, all things dinosaur. Your visit to the Flinders Discovery Centre is not complete without entering the museum to see "Hughie" the life size replica of a Muttaburrasaurus, named Queensland Fossil Emblem, who was found in the region. The museum also has a range of fossils and gems, local history, a shearing display and a movie on the formation of Porcupine Gorge. For those looking for a deeper understanding of country living, the Flinders Discovery Centre also offers Town Tours and Sunset Tours to take in the endless horizons.

## Sensory Audio Guides

Our accredited Information Centre offers a one-stop-shop for travel information, including maps, brochures and itineraries. Staffed by skilled and knowledgeable locals, the Hinchinbrook Visitor Information Centre can provide advice on things to see, things to do and where to eat and can also book your Queensland National Park camping permits. properties.name: Toowoomba Visitor Information Centre
properties.description:
The team at Toowoomba Visitor Information Centre welcome you as a valued guest; with true country hospitality and a passionate desire to help you enjoy your visit. With a wealth of local knowledge, they can give you first-hand tips for exploring the Toowoomba area; with its intriguing history, quiet natural beauty, four distinct seasons, and delicious produce. Their beautiful "Queenslander" building is based on a late 1800s style Toowoomba house. It features stained-glass motifs of the "Toowoomba" violet; which you can best enjoy by going inside. Drop in for maps, brochures, locally-produced food and artisan-made items, Toowoomba souvenirs and refreshments. On-site parking is provided for cars, coaches and caravans; adjacent to picnic and playground facilities in East Creek Park.

## Sensory Audio Guides

properties.name: Charters Towers Visitor Information Centre
properties.description:
The Charters Towers Visitor Information Centre is located at the intersection of Gill and Mosman Streets, right next to City Hall. Built-in 1880 for 2350 Pounds, the information centre started its life as the Union Bank and is just one example of the many stunning heritage buildings which line the streets of Charters Towers. Ask for a heritage walking map so that you can see first-hand the expert handiwork of the stonemasons and builders of the 19th century. Or, hire a CD or USB that will take you on a self-drive tour around the city while providing excellent commentary and information. This accredited visitor information centre offers a one-stop-shop for travel information, including maps, brochures and tour bookings. Staffed by skilled and knowledgeable locals, the Charters Towers Visitor Information Centre can provide advice on things to see, do, where to sleep and where to eat.

The centre offers maps, brochures, souvenirs, travel essentials and a huge range of giftware. They also handle bookings, including Curtis Ferry Coffee Cruise tickets, Heron Island, and local camping permits. Visit them at Marina Ferry Terminal, 72 Bryan Jordan Drive, Gladstone.

properties.name: BIG4 Conway Beach Tourist Park Whitsundays
properties.description: Conway Beach is a small community located a short 25 minute drive from Airlie Beach. Conway Beach is at the mouth of the Proserpine River, an area renowned for great fishing and crabbing. The park was established some 35 years ago for the fishermen, is set on 5 tropical acres and has undergone some major improvements in the last 10 years.

properties.name: Agnes Water Visitor Information Centre
properties.description:
The Agnes Water and Town of 1770 Visitor Information Centre is located at 71 Springs Road (in the same building as the Library and RTC) in Agnes Water. This accredited Visitor Information Centre offers a one stop shop for travel information including a wide range of maps, brochures, and itineraries. Staffed by skilled and knowledgeable locals, the Agnes Water and Town of 1770 Visitor Information Centre can provide advice on things to see, things to do and where to eat both in Agnes Water/1770 in particular and in the Gladstone Region generally. Discuss with the friendly Ambassadors your travel plans or make a booking. To find Agnes Water and Town of 1770 VIC or any of the other 116 VIC's in Queensland, download the free app "This is Queensland".
