properties.name: Boondooma Homestead and Camp
properties.description: Boondooma Homestead represents a step back to 1847 when the Lawson brothers along with Robert Alexander established the Boondooma Station. The homestead and outbuildings are still in their original location and onsite caretakers are available to provide you with a guided tour if required.

properties.name: Bjelke-Petersen Dam
properties.description: Bjelke-Petersen Dam is a concrete gravity dam located in Moffatdale near Cherbourg in the South Burnett Region, Queensland, Australia. The dam impounds Barker Creek and creates Lake Barambah. It is named after the Queensland Premier Joh Bjelke-Petersen.

properties.name: Billabong Sanctuary
properties.description:
Billabong Sanctuary is a wildlife park in North Queensland, Australia, that features over 100 species of Australian animals, including iconic species such as koalas, kangaroos, dingoes, and crocodiles. The park is known for its immersive experiences, which allow visitors to get up close and personal with some of Australia's most unique and fascinating creatures.

Billabong Sanctuary is a great place to learn about the unique fauna of North Queensland. The park offers a variety of educational programs and exhibits that teach visitors about the animals' habitats, behaviors, and conservation status.

properties.name: Australian Stockmans Hall of Fame and Outback Heritage Centre
properties.description:
Our story begins where all good stories begin, sitting around the kitchen table, catching up with family and friends, and sharing the day that was or the day to come. Sometimes we even exaggerate with theatrical flair or deliver a well-versed story with a touch of comedic expression that makes the story sound new and refreshed. 

Hear first-hand the recollections from our extensive oral history collection, transcribed diary entries from those that cut a living from a harsh environment, the changing seasons that brought heartbreak or great wealth and success. 

It was the bush that built the cities, is not a throwaway line uttered once and forgotten, it is steeped in truth, and it is captured in Australia's history books forever.

properties.name: Australian Age of Dinosaurs
properties.description:
The Australian Age of Dinosaurs Museum is home to the largest collection of Australian dinosaur fossils in the world. 

The Museum is split between three facilities, the Fossil Preparation Laboratory, Collection Room and Dinosaur Canyon.

properties.name: Achievers Walk
properties.description:
The Maryborough Walk of Achievers in Richmond and Wharf Streets was developed in three years over five stages. 

These plaques honour their pioneers, Olympians, and people from Maryborough who, through their achievements, have gone on to become extraordinary Australians in fields of education, government, culture and sport.

properties.name: Queensland Heritage Park
properties.description: 48 hour stay powered or unpowered caravan sites. Includes heritage park and museum. Unpowered $10 per night powered $15 per night. Tourist information available. No grass just coarse sand but very level and tidy. Very worthwhile place to stay for a couple of nights.

properties.name: Clifton Racecourse
properties.description: Friendly place with some congrete and grass sites. Fees should be paid at 95 King St during the week (Council Offices). On weekends the fees can be left in the box. The caretaker lives nearby.

properties.name: Loyalty Beach Campgrounds
properties.description:
Both powered and unpowered sites  are available on the 11 acres of land, with shared amenities including toilets, showers & coin operated washing machines.

Choose a spot to relax from the corrugations, on the beachfront or under the shade of the trees. Either way we're sure you'll enjoy your stay!

Loyalty Beach Campground is a pet friendly site, & all water is drinkable & ready for use.

properties.name: 1770 Southern Cross Backpackers
properties.description: 1770 Southern Cross is located on a 16 acre property only minutes from the town centre of Agnes Water. Our guests have access to the whole property and are free to roam as they wish. Find a quiet spot by the lake amongst the gardens and wildlife to sit back and relax or utilize our many grassy acres for a friendly game of football or soccer. What ever your into, its all here at Southern Cross.

properties.name: Glacier Rock via Douglas Track
properties.description:
The Glacier Rock via Douglas Track is a hiking trail located in Lamington National Park, Queensland. This scenic track offers a memorable journey through lush rainforest and sub-tropical landscapes, leading hikers to the mesmerizing Glacier Rock. 

The hike begins at the O'Reilly's Rainforest Retreat and takes you along the Douglas Track, which is well-maintained and features informative signage about the local flora and fauna. As you progress, you'll encounter picturesque waterfalls and streams. The trail gradually ascends, providing an opportunity to immerse yourself in the beauty of the rainforest. 

Upon reaching Glacier Rock, hikers are rewarded with panoramic views of the surrounding valleys and Lamington Plateau, making it an ideal spot for picnics and enjoying the natural beauty of the area. 

The Glacier Rock via Douglas Track is suitable for hikers of varying skill levels and offers a fantastic opportunity to experience the World Heritage-listed rainforest of Lamington National Park.

properties.name: Barron Falls Lookout
properties.description: The Barron Falls is a steep tiered cascade waterfall on the Barron River located where the river descends from the Atherton Tablelands to the Cairns coastal plain, in Queensland, Australia

properties.name: Ocean Beach Campground
properties.description:
Ocean Beach, the designated camping area is 16km north of the beach access point on North Street, Woorim. Campsites just behind the dunes are accessible from defined track entrances. Toilets, screened cold showers and water taps (treat water before drinking) are provided at the camping area accessed by track 'P'*. 

Please use these facilities or bring your own portable enclosed toilet system. 

A portable toilet waste disposal point is located on access 'P'  near the toilet. Fires are permitted in the fire rings in the group trailer and camping area. Generators are not permitted.

Only accessible by 4wd
properties.fees: $6.15 per person per night, or $24.60 per family per night; Permits required

properties.name: Glass House Mountains Lookout
properties.description:
Enjoy a picnic or barbecue as you soak up the viewsn from the Glass House Mountains lookout. Study the signs at the stonewall lookout area to identify the various peaks of the well-known Glasshouse Mountains. 

Gain an even better vantage point from the fire observation tower, and find out more here about the history and culture of the area.

properties.name: Mount Inkerman Scenic Lookout
properties.description:
Mount Inkerman Scenic Lookout is a must-see for any visitor to the Burdekin region of Queensland. Located just 2km off the Bruce Highway, the lookout offers stunning views of the surrounding countryside, including the Burdekin River, the Great Barrier Reef, and the Great Dividing Range.
The lookout is easily accessible by car or on foot. There is a car park at the base of the lookout, and a short walking track to the summit. There is also a picnic area and barbecue facilities at the top. Steep sealed road to a great lookout! Not for caravans, but fine for campervans. Enjoy the view and a BBQ!

properties.name: Camooweal free campground
properties.description: This is the same as the Georgina River campground. This should be deleted. I have updated the Georgina River camp to reflect what's available

properties.name: Grassy Hill Lookout
properties.description: Grassy Hill Lookout is a scenic viewpoint located in Cooktown. It offers stunning panoramic views of the town, the Endeavour River, and the Coral Sea. The lookout is accessible via a short but steep walk from the town center.

properties.name: Mount Sorrow Ridge Trail
properties.description: Mount Sorrow ridge trail, Cape Tribulation. This trail climbs from the coastal lowlands of Cape Tribulation, up the rainforest-clad ridge of Mount Sorrow to a lookout offering views of the beautiful Daintree coastline, Snapper Island and beyond.

properties.name: Archer Point
properties.description: Free campground by the sea. It's a 20 minute drive over dirt road, 4x4 needed in wet-season, otherwise accessible by any type of car. Please dump your rubbish in the bin at the entrance of the camp-area! Keep it clean!

properties.name: Burdekin Cane Farm
properties.description: A working sugar cane farm with hosts who cannot do enough for you. Took us to see a cane burn and can watch the harvesting and train loading. Gorgeous camp ground but only for self contained as there are no toilets - only power & water. Authentic outback experience. As good as it gets

properties.name: Poverty Creek (4WD only)
properties.description: This large camping area has open grassy sites and shady trees, and includes sites suitable for camper trailers and group camping. Toilets, portable toilet waste disposal facility, screened cold showers, water taps (treat water before drinking), picnic tables and fireplaces are provided. Fires are permitted in the fire rings in the group trailer and camping area.Permits are required for both camping and 4WD access

properties.name: Carmila Beach Road
properties.description:
Beach camp
Separated sites
4WD Recommended

properties.name: Lilley's Beach Campground
properties.description:
Visitors can stay within the fenced enclosed area at the northern end of Lilley's Beach. Look for evidence of an existing campsite in preference to creating another. 

Select a sandy or hard surface. The impression you leave will be almost unnoticeable on this surface.

Vehicle permits are required prior to accessing Lilley's Beach which are available from Gladstone and Calliope Administration Centres or the Boyne Tannum Community Centre. 

Permits are issued with a number of conditions and failure to comply with the conditions can result in an on-the-spot fine.

Access by 4 wheel drive, only at low tide.

The best time to travel is at low tide or within two hours either side of low tide (tidal conditions). Volunteers from the Fitzroy Basin Association’s Team Turtle CQ monitor the area annually for turtle nests from November to March.

Free to stay , but need permit for beach ($10).

properties.name: Lake Tinaroo
properties.description: Lake Tinaroo, in Queensland, Australia, is a picturesque man-made reservoir surrounded by lush rainforests. It's a haven for water sports enthusiasts, offering kayaking, fishing, and sailing opportunities. The lake's tranquil waters and scenic beauty also make it a popular spot for camping and picnicking, attracting outdoor adventurers year-round.

properties.name: Gil weir RV and camp grounds
properties.description: A free campsite for up to 2 nights right on the banks of the Dogwood Creek with limited facilities

properties.name: Zonhoven Park Rest Area
properties.description: This spacious and level overnight rest area with 20hrs stay limit has fantastic facilities, incl. hot showers and a dump point. It is located off the highway and separated from it by a wall of trees. There is plenty of shade and some lovely views over the Barnett River.

properties.name: Wallam Creek Rest Area
properties.description: Large riverside rest area with good facilities located by the river. Hot showers, laundromat, dump point and shops are available close by in town. There is a nice fishing spot, birdwatching opportunities and walking and bike tracks around. It is suitable for big rigs and donations are requested.

properties.name: Toompine Hotel Camping Area
properties.description: This scenic campground, located by a creek next to an old pub, offers hot showers and the use of powered sites. The hotel serves meals and drinks and it has become a famous destination for travelers in this area. Before setting up your camp, please introduce yourself to the staff.

properties.name: Tingoora Rest Area
properties.description: This is a very basic and large camping area with toilet facilities located off a quiet road. It has a grassy and level surface and only some shade. It is located quite close to town, with 'Tinny Pub' being its biggest attraction.Hotel has been closed for some time now

properties.name: The Royal Hotel Harrisville
properties.description: This lovely hotel offers an overnight area with good amenities and maximum stay of 96hrs. It is located by a road in a town of Harrisville. There are a few walking tracks and creek nearby, in which you can swim and fish.

properties.name: Rainbow Reserve Dumaresq River Camp
properties.description:
This grassy and open area with no facilities is located in the lagoon area, close to the road. It's a good fishing, swimming and canoeing spot. 

There is a very limited shade and it's suitable for SC vehicles only.

properties.name: Nobby Rest Area
properties.description: Pleasant area with facilities that include a playground and the use of power (extra fee, inquire at Rudds Pub). The campground is located in town, just in front of a store, cafe and a hotel. There is a train line at the back, so it might get a bit noisy. 72hrs limit apply.

properties.name: Mulgildie Hotel Camp Area
properties.description: This friendly hotel located off the highway offers a free, grassy camping area with good facilities, incl. toilets, drinking water, rubbish bins and hot showers (AUD4 pp). The pub serves tasty meals and cold drinks. There is a petrol station nearby.

properties.name: Muckadilla Community Park
properties.description: This overnight rest area with fantastic facilities is located off the highway in a small town. Hot showers are available for a fee. There is plenty of room even for big rigs, but no shade. Maximum stay is 24hrs.

properties.name: Monte Cristo Rest Area
properties.description: Drive-through sealed rest area with good facilities, located in the corner of a relatively busy junction. It's quite large and very exposed, with no shade. The traffic noise can be heard and this site is visited by truck drivers.

properties.name: Marathon Rest Area
properties.description: Exposed drive-through rest area located directly by the highway. There are toilets, rubbish bins and picnic tables, but no shade. It is popular with trucks and has 20hrs stay limit.

properties.name: Lake Victoria Biloela
properties.description: This nice bush campground with no facilities is located on the edge of the lake in a peaceful and quiet area. There is plenty of shade and both swimming and canoeing are permitted. Big rigs are not recommended. Please, take your rubbish home and leave the site as you found it.

properties.name: Kumbia Apex Park Rest Area
properties.description: Small and well-maintained rest area located just off the highway, in the centre of town. It has fantastic facilities and a playground. Donations are appreciated, especially if you use showers and power. 48hrs maximum stay.

properties.name: Junction Park Rest Area Theodore
properties.description: This is a large campground with very good amenities, located a walking distance from town and its shops and watering holes. It is situated well off the road and it is therefore quiet. It also has Dawson River at the back, providing swimming and fishing opportunities. Please leave a donation to help with the upkeep!

properties.name: Isaac River Rest Area
properties.description: This circular rest area with no facilities, except for a rubbish bin, is located off the highway. Suitable for big rigs with plenty of shade.

properties.name: Kooroorinya Nature Reserve
properties.description: Kooroorinya Nature Reserve campsite has cold showers and toilets. Located near the natural waterhole, visitors can go swimming, fishing, or go for a walk. Self- registration is required.

properties.name: Chillagoe Observatory & Eco Lodge
properties.description: Chillagoe Observatory & Eco Lodge offers two separate camping areas. One is fully grasses with scattered trees, water, power, communal kitchen, fire pits and rubbish bins. The other is an expansive partly grassed area with scattered trees,  bush showers, long drop dunnies, fire pits and rubbish bins. Bookings required for powered sites.
properties.fees: AUD $10 Adult, AUD $8 Child, AUD $2 (per person) Power

properties.name: Moonie Crossroads
properties.description:
Welcome to Moonie Crossroads!
Located in the quintessential Aussie town of Moonie – The Moonie Crossroads, Motel and Caravan Park is frequented by travellers and visitors from around the world.

A region renowned for its fishing, birdwatching, pig hunting, star gazing and of course its local farmers. Moonie provides a unique Aussie experience for every passer by, and has become a significant stopping point for weary truckies, grey nomads, tourists from around the globe, workers from all industries, the pig hunting enthusiast and fishing hopeful, Moonie Crossroads welcomes you and your family!

Air conditioned accommodation, ice cold beers on tap, tea and coffee, great steaks and an ambience that reflects our laid back, friendly attitude, come and make yourself at home!

Moonie Crossroads is located in the town of Moonie and offers motel accommodation as well as caravan and tent sites. 10 powered and 10 unpowered sites are available, with facilities including modern toilets and showers. 

For the caravan traveller, we have a large 20 site caravan park. 10 of these sites are powered. The onsite showers and toilets are clean and well maintained, and security lighting abound the property for complete peace of mind.

properties.name: Sharp Park
properties.description: James Sharp Memorial Park is a family bush camping ground situated five kilometres from the township of Canungra. Sharp Park River Bend Country Bush Camping has five hectares of managed and well maintained camping and recreational grounds set amongst the hills on the Upper Coomera River, which is ideal for swimming or throwing in a fishing line. Septic toilets on site, solar shower available on request. Campfire facilities and fire wood also available. Pets are welcome though must be contained at all times. Mount Tamborine, Lamington National Park, Killarney Glen, O'Reilly's and Binna Burra Resorts are just a few places to visit for day trips. Sharp Park is a peaceful bush camp with a country feeling. You can play cricket, kick a football or just relax and laze around. A great place to visit.
properties.fees: Off peak $9 per adult per night $3 per child per night, under 5years free Surcharge on long weekends and school holidays.  Bookings preferred but not essential.

properties.name: Andrew Drynan Park
properties.description: Andrew Drynan Park is located within Mt Chinghee National Park, along the Running Creek. Amenities include toilets, BBQs, picnic tables, and swimming. Bring your own drinking water, restrain pets, and don't use soap or detergent.

properties.name: Casuarina Camping Area
properties.description: Casuarina Camping Area is an open, grassy campground located with Glen Rock State Forest. Facilities include water, toilets, cold showers, and fireplaces. Bring your own fire wood, collection is prohibited. Permits required (call or acquire from the park office).

properties.name: Kauri Creek Campground
properties.description: Kauri Creek Campground is located within Danbulla State Forest, at the edge of an inlet. The area is ideal for swimming or canoeing. Facilities include flushing toilets, a shower room (you need to bring your own shower), and fire rings. Fires are permitted, except during fire bans; bring your own wood.

properties.name: Tamarind Gardens Tourist Park
properties.description:
6 acres, camping, caravans, fully equipped camp kitchen, showers, toilets, budget queen and twin rooms, pool, laundry, 2 bedroom cottage

Tamarind Gardens Tourist Park offers a range of accommodation, from cottages to cabins to powered and unpowered campsites. 

Facilities include a swimming pool, barbecue area, laundry, camp kitchen, hot showers, and a kiosk. Call for more information and bookings.

properties.name: Lake Coolmunda Camping Area
properties.description: Lake Coolmunda Camping Area offers shady tent sites (powered or unpowered), as well as cabins. The facilities are numerous and include flush toilets, hot showers, BBQ, kitchen, laundry, a pool, tennis courts, and water and sewage for RVs.

properties.name: Platypus Bushcamp
properties.description: Platypus Bushcamp offers quiet, spacious campsites with access to flush toilets, rainforest showers, campfires, and a picnic and cooking shelter.

properties.name: Glenlyon Dam Tourist Park
properties.description: Glenlyon Dam Tourist Park offers powered and unpowered sites, as well as cabins. Facilities include amenity blocks, barbecues, and a kiosk. If interested in fishing, boat hire is also available. Call to book and for rate enquiries.

properties.name: Eromanga Motel & Caravan Park
properties.description: Eromanga Motel & Caravan Park offers cabins, powered and unpowered sites. Facilities include flush toilets, showers, laundry, kiosk, pool, playground and barbecue area. Call for enquiries and bookings.

properties.name: Carmila Beach
properties.description: Carmila Beach currently offers $7per night camping, with toilets, barbecues, picnic tables and boat ramps. Maximum stay is three days. Payment to be made online via the park mobile app.

properties.name: Lake Murphy Conservation Park
properties.description: Lake Murphy Conservation Park offers camping with toilets, picnic tables, fireplaces and access to short walks.

properties.name: Paradise Dam
properties.description:
Enjoy boating, water skiing, or a BBQ with friends at Paradise Dam. Bring your boat and join us for some fishing—no permits required! Located 35km northwest of Biggenden and 100km southwest of Bundaberg, it's an ideal spot for family fun.

For water skiing enthusiasts, the lake offers about 25km of skiable water with a convenient boat ramp, accommodating everything from sleek ski boats to larger wake boats.

If canoeing is more your style, it's a perfect spot for a paddle. Explore the open lake or venture up one of the many nearby creeks, all within easy reach of the boat ramp.

Planning to camp? You can moor your vessel just a few meters from your campsite. Generators are allowed between 8am and 8pm

properties.name: Wilga Bush Camping Area
properties.description:
Wilga Campground is located in Lake Broadwater Conservation Park. Sites are suitable for vehicle based camping, caravans and camper trailers. 

Facilities include toilets, showers, boat ramp, picnic tables and shelter, wood fireplace and drinking water. Local activities include swimming, water-skiing, canoeing, and walking trails. 

Camping permits are required. There is a self-registration station where camping fees can be paid.

properties.name: RM Williams Australian Bush Centre
properties.description: RM Williams Australian Bush Centre offers camping on their grounds for self contained vehilces only. Pets are allowed on a lead. There is a maximum stay of 24 hours.

properties.name: Goombungee Haden Showgrounds
properties.description:
Located on Lau St., Goombungee Haden Showgrounds offers powered and unpowered sites that are suitable for big rigs. 

Facilities include gas BBQ, bins, showers, toilets and water. Enquiries can be made via phone.

properties.name: Glasbys Caravan Park
properties.description:
Glasbys Caravan Park provides powered and unpowered sites suitable for campers, caravans and motorhomes. 

Facilities include toilets, showers, BBQ, bins, campers kitchen, laundry area, and picnic tables. Bookings can be made via phone.

properties.name: Junction Park Rest Area
properties.description: Junction Park Rest area offers an overnight rest area with a maximum stay of 72 hours. Sites are suitable for tents, caravans and long rigs. Facilities include toilets, showers, drinking water, picnic tables, BBQ and boat ramp. Town is a 10 minutes walk away. Donation requested for hot showers.

properties.name: O'Shanley's Pub
properties.description: O'Shanley's Pub Camping area offers powered sites for caravans and long rigs. Facilities include toilets, water, BBQ and bins. Free caravan parking area for Hotel patrons. Bookings can be made by hpone.

properties.name: Cressbrook Dam
properties.description: Cressbrook Dam Campground provides grassy sites for tents and caravans. Facilities include BBQ, showers, boat ramp, toilets, and picnic tables. You will need to bring your own firewood. A great place for fishing and swimming. Pets are not allowed. There is a caretaker onsite.
properties.fees: $8.00 per person per night (under 5 year old free) or $32.00 per family (up to two adults and any number of children under 18yrs) per night.

properties.name: Muckadilla Community Park
properties.description: Muckadilla Community Park provides an overnight rest area that is suitable for large rigs. Facilities include hot showes (small donation), toilets, playground, BBQ and picnic tables. There is a maximum stay of 24 hours.

properties.name: Crediton Hall Campground
properties.description:
Crediton Hall Campground offers sites for vehicle based camping, and walk-in camping for up to 24 people.  It has a large, open space ideal for big rigs and RV's, surrounded by rain forest and cattle stations.

Camping area can be reached from the Mckay Highlands Great Walk. 

Facilities include toilets, water (must be treated or boiled), Pagola and BBQ and picnic tables. Generators and fires are not allowed. 

Registration on arrival or book online.

Kids stay free.

properties.name: Morven Recreation Ground
properties.description:
Morven Recreation Ground provides powered and unpowered sites suitable for tents, caravans and long rigs. Facilities include hot showers, toilets, and bins. Pets are allowed. 

Pay via honesty box.

properties.name: Eulo Queen Hotel & Caravan Park
properties.description:
Adjacent to the mighty Paroo River, in the heart of Western Queensland and boasting a colourful history, the Eulo Queen Hotel awaits the weary traveller with her old world charm and generous hospitality.  

Come in from the hot sun, enjoy a frosty cold beer and whittle an afternoon away learning about the Eulo Queen herself, the pub’s namesake. 

Her scintillating stories and newspaper clippings adorn her walls as she plays host to locals and wayfarers alike.

Eulo Queen Hotel and Caravan Park offers ensuite cabins, accommodation blocks, and a large caravan park. There are powered and unpowered sites available suitable for motorhomes and large vans. Facilities include amenities block. 

Local attractions include Paroo River and Lagoon. Activities include fishing, canoeing, bush walking, cycling and bird watching. Bookings can be made by phone.

properties.name: Hebel Store & Caravan Park
properties.description:
Hebel Caravan Park offers powered and unpowered sites for tents, caravans, hotorhomes and camper trailers. There are also cabins available for hire. 

Facilities include toilets, BBQ, showers and picnic tables. Bookings can be made by phone.

properties.name: Mulgowie Community Hall
properties.description:
This spot is a large grassed area on the Western side of the entrance track to the Mulgowie Community Hall. 
All enquiries and bookings can be made by contacting the Mulgowie Markets contact on Ph: 0498 716 102 or E: mulgowiehall@gmail.com. 
Facilities include space for caravans, powered sites, toilets and showers. The venue is also pet friendly.

properties.name: Lake Dunn Campground
properties.description:
Lake Dunn campground offers powered and unpowered sites suitable for camping and caravans. There are also cabins available for hire. Facilities include toilets, showers, laundry area, BBQ, picnic tables, boat ramp and fireplace. 

Activities include swimming, fishing, boating and canoeing. Camp fees are collected daily by the owner.

properties.name: Gin Gin Showgrounds
properties.description: Located near Lake Monduran, Gin Gin Showgrounds provides 20 powerd sites. Facilities include toilets, water, bins and laundry area. There is a caretaker on site.

properties.name: Mount Coolon Hotel
properties.description:
Our historic country pub has lots of character and memorabilia from the gold rush days.  Set amongst large cattle properties, it provides value accommodation, hearty country meals, and cold beer in the classic outback pub.

Our lunch and dinner menus offer something for everyone and you won't walk away hungry. 

Mount Coolon Hotel Campground is suitable for tents, caravns and long rigs. 

Facilities include toilets, showers, drinking water and bins. 

Pets are welcome.

We hope to see you soon.

properties.name: Muttaburra Council Caravan Park
properties.description:
Muttaburra Council Caravan Park provides powered and unpowered sites suitable for vehicle based camping, camper trailers and caravans. 

Facilities include toilets, hot showers, wood fire place and picnic tables. Dogs are permitted. Camping fees can be paid at the Muttaburra Library. Local activities include fishing, swimming and walking trails.

Fees can be paid into honesty box at Caravan Park or by visiting the Barcaldine Regional Council Administration Office and Library open on Monday to Friday from 9.00am to 4.00pm (closed for lunch from 12.00pm to 1.00pm).

properties.name: Boondooma Homestead
properties.description: Boondooma Homestead provides non-powered grass sites for all forms of camping. There are toilets available. Generators are permitted. Fees can be paid to the resident Caretaker.
properties.fees: AUD $5 per person- site entry. $5 per adult camping. Children are free. $2 per night for power

properties.name: Tomahawk Creek Fossicking Area
properties.description:
Tomahawk Creek Fossicking Area allows camping for a maximum of 3 months. 

There are no facilities available. 

You must be self-sufficient. 

A camping permit must be obtained.

properties.name: Emu Swamp Campground
properties.description: Emu Swamp Campground is located in Blackbraes Resources Reserve. It provides sites for tents, camper trailers and large groups. 4WD vehicles only. There are no facilities available. You will need to be self-sufficient. Generators are not permitted. Bookings can be made online or by phone.

properties.name: Jandowae Showgrounds
properties.description:
Jandowae Showgrounds provides powered and unpowered sites. 

Facilities include toilets and water. 

In the area there is a supermarket, cafe, post office and pubs.

properties.name: Gheerulla Campground
properties.description:
Gheerulla Campground located in Mapleton Forest Reserve provides 3 sites suitable for tents and camper trailers. 4WD vehicle is recommended. (Not suitable for caravans.) 

3 camping sites, with each site allowing a maximum of 6 people.

Facilities include toilets, picnic tables and wood BBQs. You will need to bring water and firewood and preferable a fuel stove. Open fire are allowed in BBQs only. 

Generators are not allowed.

properties.name: Theresa Creek Dam
properties.description: Theresa Creek Dam offers a nonpowered campsite suitable for caravans. Facilities include showers, toilets, BBQ, bins and picnic tables. Bookings are not necessary. Fires are allowed. Bring your own firewood. A popular place for swimming and fishing.
properties.fees: AUD $15 per couple per night. Kids are free

properties.name: Darlington Park
properties.description: Darlington Park camping area provides sites for vehicle based camping, camper trailers and caravans. Facilities include toilets, wood fireplace, playground, BBQ and picnic tables. Local activities include swimming, fishing, cycling, canoeing, and walking trails. You will need to bring your own water. Basic supplies can be purchased at the local kiosk. Bookings can be made by phone and are recommended during the peak season.

properties.name: Woodford  Showgrounds
properties.description: Woodford Showgrounds campground provides powered and unpowered sites for tents, caravans and all sized rigs. Facilities include toilets, showers, mobile phone coverage and bins. There is a maximum of 7 days. Fees and bookings must be made in advance.
properties.fees: AUD $20 for a 2 person site/powered. $15 for a 2 person site - unpowered $5 additional adult.

properties.name: Gleneden Family Farm and Bullock Team
properties.description:
Gleneden Family Farm offers private campsites, friendly farm animals, stunning views, and even a waterfall with a waterhole for swimming. Nestled in the picturesque western foothills of the Main Range, just 90 minutes from Brisbane, this 640-acre working farm is family-run and home to free-range pigs, sheep, cows, a dairy, and plenty of chickens. 

The farm also features mountain bike tracks and scenic bushwalking areas. At the farm shop, you can purchase organic pastured pork, wood-smoked nitrate-free ham and bacon, beef and lamb, as well as soaps and jams.

It provides a private, bush camping experience.

properties.name: Bowen River Hotel
properties.description: Bowen River Hotel offers a range of accomodation including hotel rooms and a camping area for tents and caravans. Facilities include

properties.name: Kogan Memorial Hall
properties.description: Camping can be arranged by either going into general store or pub.

properties.name: Mareeba Rodeo - Kerribee Park Camping
properties.description: This paid campground offers toilets, showers, drinking water, a dump point and power hookups. It is dog friendly. It is accessible to motorbikes, RVs, camper trailers, caravans and big rigs. Open from March 1st until November 30th. NO BOOKINGS REQUIRED, prices are on the website. Occasional events throughout the year may change camping arrangements, go to website or Facebook page for updates. There is a resident caretaker on site.

properties.name: Gatton Freedom Lifestyle Park
properties.description: Gatton Freedom Lifestyle Park has a lot to offer backpackers who need accommodation while working in the region.

properties.name: Rathdowney Caravan Park
properties.description: Rathdowney Caravan Park offers powered sites suitable for caravans, tents and campers. There are showers available. Pets are allowed. Advanced bookings are not required.

properties.name: Mount Hay Gemstone Tourist Park
properties.description:
Located on the Capricorn Highway, Mount Hay Gemstone Tourist Park offers a camping ground and powered caravan park. 

Facilities include BBQ area, hot showers, laundry facilities and shelter area.

properties.name: Hughenden RV Parking Area
properties.description: Hughenden RV Parking Area is suitable for self contained vehicles only. There are no facilities available. Pets are allowed. There is a maximum stay of 48 hours.

properties.name: Charlie Moreland Campground
properties.description:
Charlie Moreland Campground located in Imbil State Forest is situated on the banks of Little Yabba Creek. Sites are suitable for caravans, tents and most standard vehicles. Toilets are available. 

An ideal place for swimming and canoeing.  You will need to bring your own firewood and drinking water. Generators are not allowed.  Advanced bookings are necessary.

properties.name: The Red Lizard Camping Ground
properties.description: The Red Lizard Camping Ground offers 20 powered sites and 20 unpowered sites suitable for tents, caravans and camping trailers. Facilities include camp kitchen, amenitites block, free firewood and gift shop. Campfires are allowed. Pets are welcome. Bookings can be made online or by phone.
properties.fees: Powered sites - $30.00 max 2 people ( plus $5.00 each for kids)Unpowered sites - $25.00 max 2 people (plus $5.00 each for kids)

properties.name: Cobb and Co Nine Mile Campgrounds
properties.description: Cobb & Co Nine Mile Campgrounds offers luxury camping in canvans tents as well as unpowered campsites. Campsite facilities include toilets, showers, BBQ, and tables. There is also a kiosk that sells firewood, ice and other items. Free to use while camping are their supply of kaykas, canoes and surfboards. Campfires are permitted in allocated areas. You will need to provide your own water and towels. Bookings can be made online or by phone.
properties.fees: (luxury tents)  AUD$ 80 per couple per night  (Unpowered sites) $15 per person per night $7 per child

properties.name: Opalton Bush Camp
properties.description:
Opalton Bush Park is located 125klms south of Winton.

With wide open spaces to camp, some undercover sites, 3 x rustic huts, barbeque facilities, toilets, showers (hot water via a donkey), tank water, mobile phone coverage, friendly local miners and of course, a huge area to noodle for opal in the designated fossicking area, it's great fun.

A small shop caters for basics including bread, milk, ice, drinks and snacks.

Bird watching is very popular with rare species located in the area.

7klms of walking tracks recently installed takes you to historic sites around the area including a lookout, historic cemetery and township.

There is a beautiful dam to sit and watch the wildlife or take a swim on those hot days.

properties.name: Dimbulah Caravan Park
properties.description:
Dimbulah Caravan Park offers a large site with great gardens. It is very quiet.

It has powered sites for caravans and big rigs. Facilities include toilets, showers, drinking water, camp kitchen, bins, picnic tables and public phone.

 Pets are allowed.

properties.name: Eungella Dam Camp
properties.description: Eungella Dam campground offers basic bush camping with 50 sites available. Facilities include toilets, picnic tables, and wood BBQ. Bookings are not required. There is a self seve booth on the site. Pets are allowed. You will need to bring your own firewood. There is swimming and fishing at the nearby lake.

properties.name: Wandilla Station
properties.description: Wandilla Station is a working sheep and cattle station offering bush camping. In the area you can choose from bird watching, bush walking, fishing, among other outback activities.

properties.name: Jowalbinna Rock Art Safari Camp
properties.description:
Located on the Little Laura River, Jowalbinna Rock Art Safari Camp offers accommodation in cabins and a campground. 

Facilities include toilets, showers, and BBQ. Attractions include safe swimming in the nearby creek, sandstone escarpments, and Quinkan rock art.  4WD vehicles only. Bookings can be made over the phone.

properties.name: Toogoolawah Drop Zone
properties.description:
Skydive Ramblers offers a a variety of on-site accommodation options to suit everyone, including a bunk house with a kitchen and lounge room, 3 days free camping, powered camp sites, caravans, and self-contained motel-style rooms with ensuites. 

Camp Sites are free to jumpers for up to 3 nights. Jumpers wishing to camp longer than 3 nights will need to pay a fee of $7 a day at manifest.

Facilities include toilets, coin operated showers and laundry area. In the area you can enjoy fishing, watersports, and horse riding. If you are skydiving, the campsite is free. Bookins are essential.

properties.name: Red Rock Campground
properties.description:
Red Rock Campground in Byfield State Forest, offers sites for vehicle based camping, caravans and camper trailers (There is also a tent site nearby).

 Facilities include toilets, water (must be treated before drinking), wood fireplace and picnic tables. Open fires in existing fireplaces and small generators are allowed. 

You will need to bring your own wood.  Dogs are allowed on a lead. 

Due to crocodile sightings, swimming in not permitted in some areas. 

Bookings are essential.

properties.name: Boonah Showgrounds
properties.description: Boonah caravan park is located at the Boonah showgrounds and is a short walk to town. Facilities include showers, toilets, amenities block, laundry, camp kitchen, and free dump point.  Attractions include fishing, boating, scenic drives and bushwalking. Bookings can be made online.
properties.fees: AUD $8 per person (unpowered) $50 per week. Overnight vans $27 per night Park Special $22 per night, 3 or more nights

properties.name: Leichhardt Lagoon Camping Park
properties.description: Situated near the Normal River, Leichhardt Lagoon Camping Park provides unpowered sites for tents, camper trailers, caravans and motorhomes. Facilities include hot showers, septic toilets, BBQ, picnic tables, and water (not suitable for drinking). Generators are permitted.  The caretakers are onsite for you to register.

properties.name: Moreton Telegraph Station Camping Ground
properties.description: Moreton Telegraphic Station is located in Cape York. This campsite is suitable for tents, caravans and camper trailers. There are plenty of shady campsites throughout the grounds. Facilities include picnic tables, toilets and 3 unisex showers. There are designated fireplaces throughout the site for cooking but you must bring your own firewood with you.

properties.name: Stinson Memorial Park
properties.description: Stinson Memorial Park is located in Queensland. The site is suitable for tents, caravans and camper trailers. Facilities include picnic tables, BBQ facilities, toilets and water

properties.name: Archer River Roadhouse
properties.description: Archer River Roadhouse is a seasonal campground open over summer months. Campsites are suitable for tents, caravans and camper trailers. Facilities include picnic tables, toilets, showers and drinking water. Activities include fishing and walking.

properties.name: Booloumba Creek No.4 Campground
properties.description:
Booloumba Creek 4 camping area features on open forest setting with grass surface campsites. Camp sites are suitable for tents, vehicle based camping, caravans, camper trailers and campervans. 

Facilities include water (must be treated before drinking), toilets, individual fire rings, and walking tracks. Generators are not allowed. 

It is recommended to bring your own water, rubbish bags and insect repellent. Advanced bookings are available.

properties.name: Cooks Hut Campground
properties.description:
Cooks Hut Campground is located in Kutini-Payamu (Iron Range) National Park. During peak periods, this campsite becomes very popular. Self-registration is not available. 

Toilet facilities are provided. 

You will need to bring your own water. 

Camp sites are not suitable for caravans.

properties.name: Dandabah Campground
properties.description: Dandabah camping area offers a well-developed campground close to private facilities. The camp areae is a large, grass area suitable for vehicle based camping, walk-in camping, camper trailers and large groups. Facilities include toilets, hot showers, water (treat before drinking), picnic tables, shelter sheds, rubbish bins, and coin-operated BBQ. Nearby camp, you can enjoy walking tracks, self-guided walks and lookouts. Fires and generators are not permitted. Advanced bookings can be made.

properties.name: Lake Nuga Nuga
properties.description: Nuga Nuga bush camping ground offers an open area without defined sites. It is suitable for vehicle based camping, walk-in camping, off-road caravans, off-road camper trailers, and off-road motorhomes. There are no faciliites available. Open fires are allowed. You will need to bring your own firewood and water. Bookings are available.

properties.name: Little Boomerang Waterhole Camping Area
properties.description:
Little Boomerang Waterhole camping area, on the banks of the Barcoo River, features an open area without defined sites. Camping is suitable for camper trailers and vehicle based camping. 

Pit toilets are available. Campfire are permitted, but generators are not allowed. You will need to be self-sufficient, including drinking water.

Bookings are available.

properties.name: Moonlight Dam Camping Area
properties.description:
Moonlight Dam camping area offers a quiet environment on the edge of Moonlight Dam. This campsite has an open area without defined sites suitable for tent camping and high-clearnace camper trailers.

There are pit toilets available, open fires are prohibited and fuel stoves are recommended. You will need to bring all your own supplies, including water. Bookings are available. Mobile phone coverage is unavailable.

properties.name: Auburn River Campground
properties.description: Auburn River camping is located on the northern bank of the Auburn River. The campsite has five sites suitable for tents, camper trailers, caravans and walk-in camping. Facilities include toilets, BBQ, shelter shed, communal fires and picnic tables. Tank water is available but must be boiled before drinking. Generators are permitted. Camping permits are required and must be displayed at your camp site.

properties.name: Pyramid Campground
properties.description:
Pyramid Campground in Porcupine Gorge National Park, Queensland, offers a scenic and serene camping experience. The campground is located near the impressive Pyramid rock formation and is surrounded by dramatic cliffs and lush landscapes. It has basic facilities, including picnic tables, fire rings, and pit toilets. 

The site is suitable for tent camping and camper trailers, but there are no powered sites or showers. It's an ideal spot for nature lovers and hikers, with easy access to walking trails that lead to the gorge's natural wonders. Bookings are required.

Generators are not allowed. 

You will need to bring your own water, fuel or gas stove and rubbish bags.

properties.name: Kalpowar Crossing Camping Area
properties.description:
Kalpowar Crossing is one of Rinyirru's most popular campgrounds with 14 numbered sites for general camping. Great facilities, including toilets, showers, water,( that must be treated first) and wood fireplace. 

You will need to bring your own firewood, and generators are not permitted. Accessible by 4WD only. Bookings are required.

properties.name: Lonesome Bush Camping Area
properties.description:
The Lonesome bush camping area is set alongside the banks of the Dawson River, this camping area is a grassy area surrounded by brigalow scrub and tall open forest.

Camping area features: alongside the banks of the Dawson River, this camping area is a grassy area surrounded by brigalow scrub and tall open forest. Please note that Dawson River does not have permanent water.

Location: located approximately 4km from the lookout, access to the camping area is via the Arcadia Valley Access Road and is approximately 500m from the road.

Access: the camping area can be reached by conventional vehicles. It is accessible for trailers, campervans, motorhomes and caravans.

Number of sites: open area without separately defined sites.

Camp sites are suitable for: tent camping beside your car; walk-in camping; caravans; camper trailers, campervans and motorhomes.

Camp site surfaces: grass.

Facilities: one fire ring.

Open fires: allowed (except when fire bans apply) in fire rings only. Bring your own clean-milled firewood. Do not bring in or collect bush wood.

Generators: prohibited.

Essentials to bring: at least 7 litres of water per person per day (for drinking, cooking and washing), insect repellent, gas stove and fuel, and sealable containers for rubbish.

properties.name: Rinyirru (Lakefield) National Park
properties.description: Lakefield located on the Cape York Peninsula. Facilities include toilets, showers, BBQ, and drinking water. Camping permit required and must be booked in advance. No mobile phone coverage.
properties.fees: AUD $5.95 per person AUD $23.80 per family

properties.name: Crows Nest Camping Area
properties.description: Crows Nest Camping area is located in the Crows Nest National Park. There are 13 campsites suitable for tents, caravans, camper trailers and motorhomes. Facilities include pit toilets, wood BBQ's and showers, however you must bring your own supply of drinking water. Generators are not permitted.
properties.fees: AUD $5.95 pp or AUD $23.80 per family

properties.name: Isla Gorge Campground
properties.description: Isla Gorge camping area is suitable for tents, caravans, camper trailers and motorhomes. Facilities include composting toilets, picnic tables and fire rings. Generators are not permitted.
properties.fees: AUD $6.50 per Adult or AUD $23.80 per family

properties.name: Broadwater Campground
properties.description: Broadwater Camping area is in the Sundown National Park. Facilities include small BBQ's, pit toilets and bush showers. Bring your own drinking water. Suitable for tents, campervans and caravans. Bookings are required at all times.
properties.fees: AUD $5.95 per Adult or AUD $23.80 per family

properties.name: Broadwater Waterhole Camping Area
properties.description:
Broadwater Waterhole camping area is considered a bush campground surrounded by woodlands. Campsites are suitable for tents, caravans and camper trailers. 

There are no facilities and no drinking water. Generators are not allowed. Fees apply.
properties.fees: AUD $5.95 per adult or AUD$23.80 per family

properties.name: Bald Rock & Castle Rock Campgrounds
properties.description: Castle Rock and Bald Rock Creek camping areas are in a pleasant open forest setting close to the QPWS information centre and walking tracks. Both cater for tent camping and camper trailers. Castle Rock camping area is more suitable for caravans and motorhomes. Facilities include showers, toilets, picnic tables and communal wood BBQ's.
properties.fees: AUD$5.95 per Adult or AUD$23.80 per family

properties.name: Jourama Falls Camping Area
properties.description:
Located beside Waterview Creek, this camping area is a popular swimming and picnic spot and a good place for birdwatching. The camping area is about 300m from the park entrance, beyond the second causeway. Suitable for tent camping besides your car, caravans, camper trailers, motor homes and large groups.

Features: located beside Waterview Creek, this is a popular camping area and a good place for birdwatching.

Location: the camping area is about 300m from the park entrance, past Jourama Falls day-use area and the second causeway.

Map: Jourama Falls camping area map (PDF, 1.6MB)

Access: the camping area can be reached by conventional vehicles. It is accessible to trailers, caravans and buses.

Number of sites: open area without separately defined sites.

Camp sites are suitable for: tent camping beside your car, caravans, camper trailers, motor homes and large groups.

Camp site surface: grass.

Facilities: flush toilets, cold shower, picnic tables and gas barbecues.

Open fires: not allowed. Fuel stoves are recommended.

Generators: prohibited.

Essentials to bring: rubbish bags and insect repellent.

properties.name: Dawson River Rest Area
properties.description: This big and shaded riverside park offers a wide choice of undesignated camping areas together with fantastic facilities (incl. hot showers available at AUD1/ 2 mins). The campground is located 7km from town, where you can use a dump point and fill up on drinking water. Please make sure to leave a donation for using the park.

properties.name: Cracow Heritage Centre
properties.description: This small town offers $10 camping with fantastic facilities, including powered sites and hot showers. The donation is more than welcome and the site is suitable for SC vehicles only. You can enjoy meals and drinks served by the Cracow Hotel, too.

properties.name: Canal Creek Crossing Camping Area
properties.description: Situated on the Old Telegraph Track, this campsite is popular with 4WD aficionados. It is best to set up camp just before the Canal Creek's crossing, on the left hand side. There are no amenities and it's accessible with a 4WD only.

properties.name: Bengalla Reserve
properties.description: Great bush camp by the river that can be accessed with 4x4 vehicle (recommended, if not essential). The surface is level at the entrance, but best camping spots are located down the river bank.

properties.name: Bedford Weir Camping Area
properties.description: This campground is big but dusty with some shade. The facilities  are dated. Bring your own drinking water. Dingoes can harass dogs so watch little dogs. Max. Stay 7 days with donations required.

properties.name: Balgal Beach Rest Area - tent camping only
properties.description: Beach campground for tents only. The area is regularly patrolled by the Council and sleeping in the cars is prohibited. Good facilities and 48hrs limit.

properties.name: Archer Point Camping
properties.description: This is a beautiful place to stay overnight, however it requires a free permit that can be arranged for by phone ((07) 4069 6957) or in person at 1/99 Charlotte Street Cooktown (office hours unconfirmed). No facilities available and no pets allowed.

properties.name: Alwyn Francis Bridge Rest Area
properties.description: Large rest area located off the highway with plenty of facilities to make your stay comfortable. It can get quite noisy, but the further you go the quieter it becomes! 20hrs max stay.

properties.name: Adavale Town Hall
properties.description: Camping is permitted in the grounds of the newly renovated Adavale Town Hall. Campers have access to toilets and showers. There is also a post office, pub, shop and a museum in the immediate neighbourhood.

properties.name: Rex Range Lookout
properties.description:
Located in between Cairns and Port Douglas, Rex Lookout provides a pristine viewpoint of Trinity Bay below, and pairs as a perfect backdrop to any photo. 

It doesn't matter if you're a fan of sun and sand, this view is definitely worth the stop.

properties.name: Mena Creek Falls
properties.description:
Mena Creek Falls, located in Queensland, Australia, is a captivating natural attraction. 

Admission costs vary seasonally, with prices typically ranging from $15 to $25 AUD per adult. 

The falls cascade over lush, tropical vegetation and can be explored via well-maintained walking trails, offering a tranquil escape into the heart of the rainforest. 

Visitors can marvel at the picturesque waterfall and its serene surroundings while enjoying a peaceful day in this beautiful natural setting.

properties.name: Darr River Rest Stop
properties.description: Basic roadside and riverbank stop with toilet and rubbish bin provided.

properties.name: Funny Dunny Campground
properties.description:
Located 300 metres from the beach, Funny Dunny Campground offers sites for tents, caravans and long rigs. Facilities include toilets and wood fireplace. There is a maximum stay of 48 hours. 

Camping is available for $5 per night per site (1 caravan or tent or camper per site) to assist in maintaining the campground. No power or drinking water is available at this campground.

properties.name: Roadside Gravel Area
properties.description: Small entrance to this gravel pit, drive slowly to not miss it. There are not many places to turn around. It's a spacious area with good spots to hide behind trees or sand piles to belittle road noise. No facilities, take your rubbish home.

properties.name: Cape River Roadside Stop
properties.description: Basic stopping bay along the highway. Not meant to be for camping, but okay to stay if tired. No facilities. Gravel bay accessible for all kinds of vehicles, heavy road noises, no shadowy areas.

properties.name: Einasleigh River Rest Area
properties.description: This hidden campsite at Einasleigh river requires an almost 40km gravel road drive. Road is partly rough and a big effort in a 2WD. It's a peaceful spot right after the bridge on your right. No facilities except a very old picnic table. Take care with high vehicles as branches might be in your way. Camping on a little plateau between the trees. Lots of cattle around. 4WD highly recommended.

properties.name: 8 Mile Creek Camping
properties.description: Located a few hundred meters off the highway, at creek. Access a but steep, better check before driving down. No facilities, SC only. Peaceful place for 5 - 10 cars, no road noises. Direct access to creek. Check for space before driving down. Please take your rubbish home.

properties.name: Federation Park
properties.description: Gazebo x 3, electric BBQ, covered playground equipment, walking trails

properties.name: Wallangarra Lions Park
properties.description:
Free roadside rest area in Wallangarra on New England Hwy. Toilets, picnic tables and rubbish bin available but very little shade. Also a children's playground there.

***REPORTS OF NO CAMPING SIGNS***

properties.name: Wondai RV Stop
properties.description: RV rest stop in the centre of Wondai on Haly St, adjacent to art gallery. Coin operated showers and toilets available. Max stay: 48hrs.

properties.name: Gilbert River Rest Area
properties.description: Rest area on the W bank of Gilbert River on the N side of Gulf Developmental Rd. No facilities available but some shade. Max stay: 48hrs.

properties.name: Isaac River Rest Area
properties.description: Rest area off Peak Downs Hwy just N of Issac River. Picnic tables and bins available. Located 80km SW of Nebo.

properties.name: Injune Rodeo Ground Camping
properties.description: Gravel camping area at the Injune rodeo grounds. Toilet facilities available. All kinds of vehicles, no trucks. Area is at the rear right of the showgrounds. Lights are on all night. Quiet place, even though road is close. Toilets are right next to the camping area. Good place for a night, but not the most charming spot.

properties.name: Bungeworgorai Creek
properties.description: Simple rest area off Warrego Hwy next to the creek. No facilities, some shade from trees. Located 10km W of Roma.

properties.name: Paroo River
properties.description: Large free camping area on both sides of the Paroo River bridge. Picnic table and some shade available. Located on Bulloo Developmental Rd, 68km W of Cunnamulla.

properties.name: Crawford Creek Rest Stop
properties.description: Large parking area for both SC and non-SC vehicles. Toilets on site

properties.name: TYTO Self Contained RV Park
properties.description:
The TYTO RV Park site is open from 1 March to 30 November. The Park is located near the TYTO Wetlands, home to 27.4% of Australian bird species. Permits are $15 per vehicle per night and must be obtained from the Hinchinbrook Visitor Information Centre prior to setting up.  TYTO RV Park site is close the walking tracks of the TYTO Wetlands.

Potable water is available. We have a 72 hour stay policy.  Please no tents.

properties.name: Stubby Bend Camp
properties.description: This large and open campsite sits on the Barcoo River bank, only 1 km away from town. There are no amenities, other than picnic tables and rubbish bins, however there are plenty of water activities on offer and walking is great, too. This campsite is available to self-contained campers only and a 72hrs limit applies.

properties.name: Broadwater Recreational Reserve
properties.description: The beautiful Broadwater Camping Reserve is best when not wet. Beyond the gate (please always keep it closed) there are many nice sites to stay underneath the trees along the river. Please only use this spot if SC, because there are no facilities. It is a beautiful and very quiet area, please keep it clean.

properties.name: WW2 Airfield
properties.description: Large dirt rest area near monument on Barkly Hwy. Toilets, sheltered picnic tables, bins and a dump point here. Lots of space to park, some shade from trees. 55km N of Mt Isa. Max stay: 48hrs.

properties.name: Coronation Hotel Toobeah
properties.description: Parking area behind the hotel, free to patrons of the pub. Please check in at bar before parking. Toilets and showers available, with meals and drinks available for purchase. Located on Barwon Hwy in Toobeah.

properties.name: The Bend
properties.description: Bush camping area just N of Peninsula Developmental Rd, on the banks of Coen River. Toilets available, no other facilities but it is a nice spot for fishing. Located 3km N of Coen.

properties.name: Thiess Park Camping
properties.description: Large grassy camping reserve for both SC and non-SC. Has a toilet. Max stay: 48hrs.

properties.name: Sapphire Reserve Rest Area
properties.description: Large parking area for both SC and non-SC vehicles. Max stay: 48hrs in a 7 day period. Toilets, dump station on site.

properties.name: Lake Elphinstone
properties.description: Large dirt camping area on the W banks of Lake Elphinstone. Toilets, cold showers, picnic tables and bins available, limited shade. Great spot for boating and fishing. Located on Suttor Developmental Rd, 60km W of Nebo.

properties.name: First Settlers Park Rest Area
properties.description: This large, grassy rest area with good facilities is located close to the highway and Brisbane Valley Rail Trail. Hot showers and power are available for a small fee. 20hrs max stay applies.

properties.name: Warroo Bridge Camping Area
properties.description: Camping between the trees along the Balonne River, on two sides of Warroo Bridge. No facilities, SC only. There are various level areas, some grassy, others gravel. Suitable for all types of vehicles and tents. 10km gravel road in good condition to get there. Beautiful spot, very peaceful. Please don't leave any rubbish.

properties.name: One Lane Bridge Rest Area
properties.description: Simple rest area on New England Hwy, next to the bridge. Picnic tables and some shade from trees available. Located 20km SE of Cooyar.

properties.name: Royal Hotel Parking
properties.description:
Large grassy parking area (cannot park on grass, only pitch tent on grass. 

The rest is dirt/mud depending on rain) for both SC and non-SC vehicles. Toilets, BBQ and picnic tables located across the road. Max stay: 48hrs.

properties.name: Ward River
properties.description: Free bush camping on the banks of the river. No facilities except rubbish bins, but a good spot for fishing. Some shade from trees. Located on Diamantina Developmental Rd, 20km SW of Charleville. Signposted.

properties.name: Macrossan Park Rest Area
properties.description: Large campsite available to both SC and non-SC vehicles. Max stay: 7 days. Toilets on site.

properties.name: Balonne Minor Bridge Camp
properties.description: Simple rest area on the E bank of the river. No facilities but there is some shade from trees and you can fish in the river. Located just off Bollon Dirranbandi Rd, 2km SW of Dirranbandi.

properties.name: Poll Crandell Park Rest Area
properties.description: Large grassy rest area at the park on Brisbane Valley Hwy. Sheltered picnic tables and bins here, some shade from trees. No toilets, but there are some nearby back in town. Lots of space. Located at the S end of Toogoolawah, 16km N of Esk.

properties.name: Emu Creek Campground
properties.description:
Large, open grassy rest area in Benarkin State Forest. Toilets, picnic tables and cold showers available, plenty of shade from trees. Located 15km SE of Blackbutt via Forest Drive. Dirt road. Max stay: 14 days.
Must prebook online before arrival.

properties.name: Avondale Homestead Tavern
properties.description:
Free camping in the paddock, large and grassy area. 

Free shower and toilets available. Rubbish bins and picnic places. 

Friendly staff in the pub, reasonably priced meals.
properties.fees: Free, facilities paid at $5 ($15 key deposit required)

properties.name: Oma Waterhole
properties.description: Low cost camping on the banks of Barcoo River. Toilets and hot showers here, and it is a very popular spot for fishing. 12km W of Isisford via St. Helena St.
properties.fees: $5 a night or $27 a week payable at the Council Office in Isisford weekdays or Andos Food Barn weekends.

properties.name: Round Water Hole Rest Area
properties.description: Basic rest area just off Chinchilla-Wondai Rd next to the waterhole. Picnic tables and bins here, some shade from trees. Not good in wet weather. Located 5km E of Chinchilla. Max stay: 24hrs.

properties.name: Thomson River
properties.description: Basic camp area on the banks of the river. No facilities, but it's a nice spot for fishing and there is some shade from trees. At the W end of Jundah, located on both sides of the Thomson Developmental Rd bridge.

properties.name: Bowenville Reserve Camp Area
properties.description: This spacious creek side campground is located 4km from the signposted access point. There aren't many trees and the site is quite open. Good facilities include flushing toilet, but no water taps. 7 day max stay.

properties.name: Collinsville Showgrounds
properties.description: Large and safe campsite close to town, located just across the road from great facilities. This campground is relatively quiet and dedicated to SC vehicles only. There is a dump point and town water on site. Showers and toilets are based in the Workers Club and are subject to AUD1 fee. 72 hrs max stay applies.

properties.name: Lawless Park Rest Area (Booubyjan)
properties.description: This rest area is located at the highway and provides a sheltered picnic bench as well as a rubbish bin. No toilets available.

properties.name: Jimbour Rest Area
properties.description: Gravel rest area in Jimbour. Toilets, sheltered picnic tables and bins available, with some shade from trees. Located next to War Memorial Hall on Dalby-Jandowae Rd. Max stay: 20hrs.

properties.name: Cecil Plains Apex Park
properties.description:
Spacious and level campsite with good amenities, located on the banks of the Condamine River. 

A 1km bike path will take you right to the middle of town in no time. Max stay limit is 72 hrs.

properties.name: Bungunya Rest Area
properties.description: Free rest stop just S of Barwon Hwy in Bungunya. Toilets, showers, sheltered picnic tables, BBQs and bins available. Located on Main St at N end of town, with lots of space to park. Max stay: 48hrs.

properties.name: Norman River Reserve
properties.description: Simple dirt rest area on Burke Developmental Rd. On NE bank of river, no facilities. Permit required from Info Centre to stay here. Located at the N entrance to Normanton. Max stay: 48hrs.

properties.name: Alwyn Francis Bridge Area
properties.description: Free spot beside the Stuart River 10km SW of Kingaroy on the Bunya Hwy.   Dump point in Lions Park, Kingaroy.

properties.name: Bang Bang Rest Area
properties.description: Wide access to a large area, on shingle but would suit all vehicle sizes. 3 toilets (1 has wheel chair access), 3 shelters with tables and seating.  Dump station, water available at times, rubbish bins. Extra large area at rear with some shelter from trees, set back from road a little, tidy site.

properties.name: Ooline Park
properties.description: Simple dirt rest area on the S side of Warrego Hwy. Toilets and picnic tables available. Limited space, small vehicles only. Max stay: 24hrs.

properties.name: Nobby Town Park
properties.description: Free rest area in Nobby, opposite the hotel. Toilets, picnic tables and bins available. Pay for power at the hotel. Max stay: 72hrs.

properties.name: Maidenwell Rest Area
properties.description: Camp area on Kingaroy-Cooyar Rd in Maidenwell with toilet, picnic table and bin facilities available. Showers available for a fee in hall across the road. 18km N of Cooyar. Max stay: 48hrs.

properties.name: Eastbound Lane campsite
properties.description: This site is suitable for self contained campers only as there are no toilets on site. The site is on the Eastbound side of the highway. Once you turn in there is a bumpy dirt road. If you follow that road it will take you to a paved road. Off the paved road are heaps of paved flat sites. This site is incredibly large with heaps of privacy for everyone.

properties.name: Belyando Rest Area
properties.description: Basic roadside paking area suitable for SC only. Picnic table and shelter on site.

properties.name: Black Stump Rest Area
properties.description: Large parking area available for both SC and non-SC vehicles. Max stay: 20hrs. Park up at the top near toilets. Playground here for kids.

properties.name: Wanco Station
properties.description: Camping area at Lake Houdraman. Picnic table and rubbish bins available. To access, turn N off Developmental Rd onto Old Avadale Rd. Turn right onto Lake Houdramann Rd and travel for 2km to the camp area.

properties.name: Cape River Rest Stop
properties.description: Spacious rest area along the highway. Toilet, sheltered picnic benches and rubbish bins available. Gravel area with a few trees to park in the shade. Well-established as it is one of only a few having a toilet. Might be crowded, don't arrive too late. Road noises appear, road trains at night. Great place to stay overnight with a good atmosphere.

properties.name: Fassifern Memorial Reserve
properties.description: Large rest area on Cunningham Hwy with some shade available. Suitable for all vehicle sizes. Toilet, rubbish bin  and picnic table facilities available. Located 7km S of Silverdale or 4km N of Aratula. Max stay: 20hrs.

properties.name: The Retreat Hotel Rest Area
properties.description:
The Retreat Hotel welcomes RV patrons to park on the grassy edge near the top of the road, closest to the pub. Please note that this land is owned by Main Roads.

IMPORTANT: Do not park on the wider tarred area further down, as it’s reserved for road trains to turn around.

The Retreat Hotel offers a variety of meals, cold beer, and occasional 'impromptu' entertainment. An electric guitar and amplifier are available for any patrons who can play.

Restroom facilities are available only to paying guests.

properties.name: Parkhurst Motel and Vanpark
properties.description: Clean amenities, nice stuff, very good and cheap chips, all in all a good spot for a few days

properties.name: Bingil Bay Campground
properties.description: Bingil Bay Campground is located in Queensland. This is a small campsite suitable for tents and smaller caravans and camper trailers. Facilities include picnic tables, toilets, showers and limited water supply. Bring your own drinking water.

properties.name: Booyal Roadhouse Free Camping
properties.description: Gary, the friendly owner of this place, lets people stay on his area for free as long as they want. He provides toilets, tap water, his restaurant to buy food for a fair price as well as BYO food and sit inside. His area is very clean and he gives everyone a warm welcome and offers his help. He will show you around and explains how everything works. Rubbish and recycling bins available. There is lots of space on level grassy area, also good for tents. No surcharge on foreign credit cards and ATM available. Shower and kitchen are on his to-do list. Only negative is road noise as his area is right along the highway.

properties.name: Boynedale Bush Camp
properties.description: Free bush camp located E of Boyendale. Toilets, picnic tables and some shelter provided, take your rubbish with you. There is also a lookout that provides great views of Lake Awoonga. To get there, turn S off Dawson Hwy onto Gladston-Monto Rd (4km W of Calliope). Travel this road for 26km and look out for signs for the camp turnoff on your left. Max stay: 7 days.

properties.name: PK Park
properties.description:
On the southern entry to Gympie, Next to Museum and duck ponds - just off highway.

 - late access ok, just give us a ring - drive ups ok, phone number next to gate, call us 

12 sites, > 6 Large sites, able to take big rigs and large vans.

- next door to the Gympie Mining Museum and Duck ponds 

- 4 minutes' drive to the Historic Gympie Rattler Station 

- Five minutes' drive to Gympie Main Street

properties.name: Twin Gums Caravan Park
properties.description:
Located 2 1/2 hours from Brisbane, Twin Gums Caravan Park is a great base in exploring Nanango and the South Burnett Areas. The park offers cozy accommodations - cabins, onsite vans, caravan and camping sites nestled amongst lovely shady trees.

Beautiful campsite for one night. Lovely elderly host, does this for 30 years.

properties.name: Theodore Sports & Recreation Grounds
properties.description:
Large camping area with plenty of room for big rigs. Modern clean amenities, electric bbq's under cover including sink & kettle. 

No need to book, just find a spot, the caretakers come around every afternoon.

properties.name: Laidley Showgrounds
properties.description:
The Showgrounds are located on the banks of the Laidley Creek, The Showgrounds are located on the banks of the Laidley Creek, surrounded by crop land. Conveniently within walking distance to the Laidley CBD. Large flat grassed areas for ease of parking. 

Tents and caravans welcome.

properties.name: Boodua reserve
properties.description: Dry weather track only, drop toilets, a bit overgrown but right on the banks of the river. Open fireplaces & picnic tables provided 4wd access recommended after rain. Suitable for high clearance caravans & camper trailers

properties.name: Spring Creek Caravan Park
properties.description:
Situated on the New England Highway between Toowoomba and Warwick, Spring Creek Caravan Park offers picturesque grassy powered sites and cozy cabins. 

The well-maintained facilities include a camp kitchen, covered BBQ and picnic area, and laundry services. Designed with the traveling nomad in mind, the park provides a comfortable stay.

properties.name: Dalby Tourist Park
properties.description:
Popular park set on the bank of Myall Creek in the centre of town. Short 5 minute stroll to shops and CBD. Adjacent aquatic centre and bowls club. 2 minutes drive to golf club, race course and sporting ovals. Caravans need not unhitch. Up-market modern cabins.


Van Park Facilities
- Large sites - touring vans need not unhitch
- Sites for large motor homes
- Grassy creekside sites, some with slabs
- Ensuited powered sites
- Unpowered grassed camping areas
- Spotless amenities
- Laundry
- Dump Point
- Camp kitchen with free undercover barbeque area
- Full mobile phone and TV reception
- Pets are welcome

properties.name: Alau Beach Campground
properties.description:
Alau Beach Campgrounds, Umagico
Absolute beachfront camping overlooking the Torres Strait and its beautiful islands
Shaded and grassed powered and unpowered sites

Clean amenities, hot showers, coin operated laundry

Pet friendly

Full Telstra and internet coverage and local supermarket open 7 days

Launch your boat from the beach and fish the reef just 200 m offshore

3 km from Injinoo and 5 mins from Bamaga – 40km to The Tip

We have a saltwater in ground pool, kiosk with souvenirs, bait, ice, ice creams, drinks etc.

properties.name: Childers Nature Camp
properties.description:
Come enjoy our nature camp set up for Tents, Caravans & Motorhomes with large sites, walking tracks and an abundance of wildlife nature at its finest. 

Offering Mobile RV pre & post purchase Inspections, Repairs, Parts & Accessories. Not a nudist camp.

properties.name: Mt Fox Campground
properties.description:
Located south-west of Ingham, Mount Fox was created by a violent volcanic explosion about 100000 years ago. In the explosion, a lava flow 10 metres thick spewed from the southern end of the crater and chunks of molten magma were thrown out of the volcano's vent.

Today, the well formed crater, about 10 metres deep, is covered with sparse grasses and stunted trees amongst the eucalypt woodland environment. The pink and long-fruited bloodwoods are common in this area and vine thicket is found in a steep gully on the southern slopes.

Mount Fox's tussock grass slopes shelter a number of small animals. On a cool day in the winter months, skinks and other reptiles can be seen basking on the volcanic bombs. During the hot summer months, the grass provides protection from the sun and are ideal nesting places for ground-dwelling birds like the little button quail. After sunset, rufous bettongs (small wallaby-type mammals) emerge to feed on herbs and grasses. The large wing span of a wedge-tailed eagle can also be seen, as this bird of prey soars above the Mount Fox crater.

properties.name: Kalpowar State Forest
properties.description:
Kalpowar camping area features a tranquil bush setting beside Crane Creek. The open grassy camp sites are suitable for families and large groups.

Features: picnic or camp in a tranquil bush setting beside Crane Creek. The open grassy camp sites are suitable for families and large groups.

Location: 1.3km from the Gin-Gin Kalpowar Road.

Access: the camping area can be reached by conventional vehicles; trailers; caravans; buses; and motor homes only in dry conditions. Please check road conditions before booking your site.

Number of sites: open area without separately defined sites.

Camp sites are suitable for: tent camping beside your car; caravans; camper trailers; (small) motor homes; large groups.

Camp site surface: grass.

Facilities: tank water must be treated before drinking, pit toilets, picnic tables, communal fire rings, must bring own firewood, no rubbish bins.

Open fires: allowed in fire rings only (except when fire bans apply). Fuel or gas stoves are recommended.

Generator use: allowed. Please be considerate of your neighbours. Generators that operate at a noise level less than 65dB(A) at 7m are permitted. Generators must be shut down by 10pm.

Essentials to bring: adequate food and drinking water, rubbish bags, insect repellent, sunscreen, fuel stove and adequate fuel.

properties.name: Proston Overnight Stay
properties.description:
A great free overnight camp at Proston located in a calm shady area.

Bins provided, playground and parkland with public toilet amenities just a short walk away.

Also closely located to Main Street, with a supermarket, pub, newsagency, Department Store, coffee shop Jacaranda Tearooms and local chemist, Proston Health & Beauty.

properties.name: Millmerran Showgrounds
properties.description:
Plenty of room, power and water there is showers and toilets.

Please enter via Gate 1.

properties.name: Ferns Hideaway Resort
properties.description: Large grassy campground suitable for Caravans, camper trailers and tent camping available. Basic Camp kitchen, fire pits , day lounge and toilets with hot showers. Also available Traditional log style spa cabins with en-suite bathrooms, open fires , satellite TV and air- con.  Canoeing, full size tennis court, pool with hot spa all free for your enjoyment. Weekend restaurant  with live music.

properties.name: Fern Flat Camping Area
properties.description:
The Fern Flat camping area is located beside Broken River, where you may be able to spot a platypus.

Mobile Phone reception is available at Eungella township or at Sky Window.

Camping area features: camp beside Broken River, where you may be able to spot a platypus.

Location: 600m from Broken River day-use area, which is about 5km from Eungella township.

Access: can be reached by conventional vehicles, 600m along the gravel road.

Number of sites: 8 sites. Maximum 4 people per site.

Camp sites are suitable for: tent camping, a short walk from your vehicle. Not suitable for camper trailers, caravans or motorhomes.

Camp site surface: grass and dirt.

Facilities: hybrid toilet in camping area. Nearby day-use area has toilet facilities, information centre, picnic tables and gas barbecues. All water must be treated before drinking or using for cooking.

Open fires: allowed in fire rings only (except when fire bans apply). Fuel stoves are recommended. Bring your own clean milled timber.

Generators: not allowed.

Essentials to bring: all food and drinking water, sturdy rubbish bags, insect repellent, sun protection, first-aid kit and reliable torch.
